ACLAppliesTo.name: ACLAppliesTo
ACLAppliesTo.description: This textual convention defines the possible states for an access control group, list, or record as pertains to whether it applies to the volume, snapshots, or both.

SiteIndex.name: SiteIndex
SiteIndex.description: This textual convention defines a greater than zero value used to identify an external group operating autonomously from the local group.

SiteIndexOrZero.name: SiteIndexOrZero
SiteIndexOrZero.description: This textual convention is an extension of the SiteIndex convention. The latter defines a greater than zero value used to identify an external group operating autonomously from the local group. This extension permits the additional value of zero. the value zero is object-specific and must therefore be defined as part of the description of any object which uses this syntax. Examples of the usage of zero might include situations where the site is unknown or not relevant

ReplSiteQuotaType.name: ReplSiteQuotaType
ReplSiteQuotaType.description: The format of the adminQuota value: 0 - Unlimited quota, 1 - Size in Megabytes.

StatusEnabledDefault.name: StatusEnabledDefault
StatusEnabledDefault.description: This textual convention can be used to define a status of enabled or disabled. The value 0 is assigned to enabled

StatusDisabledDefault.name: StatusDisabledDefault
StatusDisabledDefault.description: This textual convention can be used to define a status of enabled or disabled. The value 0 is assigned to disabled

StatusAutoDefault.name: StatusAutoDefault
StatusAutoDefault.description: This textual convention can be used to define a status of auto, enabled and disabled. The value 0 is assigned to auto

VirtualVolumeType.name: VirtualVolumeType
VirtualVolumeType.description: This textual convention defines the possible values for virtual volume type

EQLRowPointer.name: EQLRowPointer
EQLRowPointer.description: Short row pointer that points to a row in one of the EQL proprietery MIBs. For cases when a column in table X will always refers to a row in table Y a the generic RowPointer is not space efficient. Storing the full OID means, the same OID prefix is repeated for each row in table Y. This type provides a more compact but context sensitive way of storing row pointers unlike the standard RowPointer. Essentially it stores just the instance index of the row it is pointing to, and not the full table OID. i.e. stores the relative path and not the absolute path. Size is 12 bytes, so it can store a pointer to a row that has 3 or less parts to its instance index. Example: If storing pointer to the eqliscsiVolumeTable. This table has an index with 2 parts eqliscsiLocalMemberId.eqliscsiVolumeIndex. byte[4-7]: eqliscsiLocalMemberId byte[8-11]: eqliscsiVolumeIndex

EQL2PartRowPointerStr.name: EQL2PartRowPointerStr
EQL2PartRowPointerStr.description: Short row pointer that points to a row in one of the EQL proprietery MIBs. For cases when a column in table X will always refers to a row in table Y a the generic RowPointer is not space efficient. Storing the full OID means, the same OID prefix is repeated for each row in table Y. This type provides a more compact but context sensitive way of storing row pointers unlike the standard RowPointer. Essentially it stores just the two part instance index of the row it is pointing to, and not the full table OID. i.e. stores the relative path and not the absolute path. The base type is a DisplayString using dot notation, .x.y, where x and y are each unsigned integers representing the components of a 2 part complex table index. Max size of the string is 23 to accommodate the max digits for 2 unsigned integers plus an '.' to separate and prepend the 2 unsigned integers plus 1 to accommodate null terminator. Example: If storing pointer to the eqliscsiVolumeTable. This table has an index with 2 parts .eqliscsiLocalMemberId.eqliscsiVolumeIndex

VirtualVolumeSnapshotStatus.name: VirtualVolumeSnapshotStatus
VirtualVolumeSnapshotStatus.description: This textual convention defines the possible virtual volume snapshot status

VirtualVolumeCreatedAs.name: VirtualVolumeCreatedAs
VirtualVolumeCreatedAs.description: This textual convention defines the possible virtual volume created as values

eqliscsiVolumeTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeTable
eqliscsiVolumeTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Volume Table. This table contains a list of volumes in a group and their attributes. TimeoutCreate:60 TimeoutDelete:60

eqliscsiVolumeIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeIndex
eqliscsiVolumeIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing a volume.

eqliscsiVolumeRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiVolumePsvId.name: eqliscsiVolumePsvId
eqliscsiVolumePsvId.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field is for internal use only.

eqliscsiVolumeName.name: eqliscsiVolumeName
eqliscsiVolumeName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies a user friendly name for a volume. The name must be unique within a group. The name must not contain spaces or special characters. The name can be up to 64 characters in length. There is no default.

eqliscsiVolumeSite.name: eqliscsiVolumeSite
eqliscsiVolumeSite.description: This field specifies the site where the volume resides. Sites are defined on a per array basis. Sites are used to define where primary and secondary copies of volume mirror reside. The default is the default site. This means that the location of the volume is unrestricted.

eqliscsiVolumeDescription.name: eqliscsiVolumeDescription
eqliscsiVolumeDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details about the volume. The description can be up to 128 characters. There is no default value.

eqliscsiVolumeAccessType.name: eqliscsiVolumeAccessType
eqliscsiVolumeAccessType.description: This field specifies access rights for the volume. The volume can be either read-write or read-only. The default is read-write.

eqliscsiVolumeSize.name: eqliscsiVolumeSize
eqliscsiVolumeSize.description: This field specifies the volume size in MB. There is no default. Note: Volume size is round to a multiple of 15MB. For thin provisioned volumes this value represents the advertized size of the volume and eqliscsiVolumeMinThinReserve represents the actual reserved size.

eqliscsiVolumeAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeAdminStatus
eqliscsiVolumeAdminStatus.description: This field specifies if the volume is set to online or offline by the administrator. If a volume is offline, it cannot be accessed by iscsi initiators. When lost blocks that belong to a particular volume are found, the operational status of the volume is set to not-available-due-to-lost-cached-blocks. When the volume is in this state, If the user chooses to ignore the lost blocks by setting the volume status to online, the admin status is automatically set to online-lost-cached-blocks by the subsystem. The online-lost-cached-blocks state of admin status conveys the fact that user acknowledged and acted up on the lost-blocks state of the volume. Upon reboot, when the subsystem finds a volume with adminstatus as online-lost-cached-blocks , it sets the oper status to online instead of not-available-due-to-lost-cached-blocks as the user already acknowledged the lost-blocks and choose to ignore them.

eqliscsiVolumeReservedPercentage.name: eqliscsiVolumeReservedPercentage
eqliscsiVolumeReservedPercentage.description: This field specifies what percentage of the volumesize will be reserved for SnapShots. This space is reserved in addition to the space reserved for the volume. The default is 100 percent.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapWarningLevel.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapWarningLevel
eqliscsiVolumeSnapWarningLevel.description: This field specifies when to warn the Administrator that the space reserved for SnapShots. The warning is sent when the SnapShot Space available drops below the specified percentage. The default is 20 percent.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapDeletionPolicy.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapDeletionPolicy
eqliscsiVolumeSnapDeletionPolicy.description: This field specifies what should happen when the space reserved for SnapShots is exhuasted. The default is delete-oldest SnapShots.

eqliscsiVolumeAutoloadBalancing.name: eqliscsiVolumeAutoloadBalancing
eqliscsiVolumeAutoloadBalancing.description: This field specifies whether or not the volume should be load balanced across multiple arrays. The default is load balancing is enabled.

eqliscsiVolumeTargetAlias.name: eqliscsiVolumeTargetAlias
eqliscsiVolumeTargetAlias.description: This field specifies the iSCSI alias used for the volume. This field defaults to the volume name.

eqliscsiVolumeTargetIscsiName.name: eqliscsiVolumeTargetIscsiName
eqliscsiVolumeTargetIscsiName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies the iSCSI target name for the volume. This name is auto-generated, though users can override the name.

eqliscsiVolumeNodeIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeNodeIndex
eqliscsiVolumeNodeIndex.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify this particular node within the ISCSI mibs. Instances of objects in those MIBS that are related to this iSCSI target will have this value of iscsiNodeIndex

eqliscsiVolumeHdrDigests.name: eqliscsiVolumeHdrDigests
eqliscsiVolumeHdrDigests.description: An object used by the manager to enable the use of iSCSI header digests for this volume. When set to 'true' the iSCSI implementation will negotiate the use of header digests with initiators. By default this feature will be turned off

eqliscsiVolumeDataDigests.name: eqliscsiVolumeDataDigests
eqliscsiVolumeDataDigests.description: An object used by the manager to enable the use of iSCSI data digests for this volume.When set to 'true' the iSCSI implementation will negotiate the use of data digests with initiators. By default this feature will be turned off

eqliscsiVolumeCloneSrcPsvId.name: eqliscsiVolumeCloneSrcPsvId
eqliscsiVolumeCloneSrcPsvId.description: If non-empty, then this volume is a clone of another volume and is waiting for the data to be copied to it. This field is the PsvId of the source volume. If value of this field is the empty string then this volume is not a clone, OR is a clone already populated with the source data.

eqliscsiVolumeReplService.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplService
eqliscsiVolumeReplService.description: Specifies the type of replication services that are provisioned on the related volume. A volume may either be a replica, a primary copy, a replication control target, or nothing at all. Regular replicasets on secondary site can be promoted to failover volumes.

eqliscsiVolumeMultInitiator.name: eqliscsiVolumeMultInitiator
eqliscsiVolumeMultInitiator.description: Specifies if the access from multiple initiators is allowed for the volume.

eqliscsiVolumeStoragePoolIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeStoragePoolIndex
eqliscsiVolumeStoragePoolIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying a storage pool. Thin clones get their pool index from the parent template.

eqliscsiVolumeStoragePoolSourceIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeStoragePoolSourceIndex
eqliscsiVolumeStoragePoolSourceIndex.description: This field specifies the source storage pool for the volume. If non-zero, the volume is currently being moved from the indicated source pool to the target pool (eqliscsiVolumeStoragePoolIndex).

eqliscsiVolumeTargetLocalMemberId.name: eqliscsiVolumeTargetLocalMemberId
eqliscsiVolumeTargetLocalMemberId.description: This field specifies the first part of a unique index for identifing an iSCSI target.

eqliscsiVolumeTargetIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeTargetIndex
eqliscsiVolumeTargetIndex.description: This field specifies the second part of a unique index for identifing an iSCSI target.

eqliscsiVolumeThinProvision.name: eqliscsiVolumeThinProvision
eqliscsiVolumeThinProvision.description: This field specifies if the Volume is enabled for Thin Provisioning.

eqliscsiVolumeMinThinReserve.name: eqliscsiVolumeMinThinReserve
eqliscsiVolumeMinThinReserve.description: This field specifies the amount of pool free space that is currently reserved for this Thin Provisioned Volume configured as percentage of eqliscsiVolumeSize.

eqliscsiVolumeThinWarnPercentage.name: eqliscsiVolumeThinWarnPercentage
eqliscsiVolumeThinWarnPercentage.description: This field specifies the percentage of Advertised Size for which we send a WARNING Message when the Allocated Volume Size reaches it. Default value is eqlGroupDefaultThinWarn.

eqliscsiVolumeThinMaxGrowPercentage.name: eqliscsiVolumeThinMaxGrowPercentage
eqliscsiVolumeThinMaxGrowPercentage.description: This field specifies the percentage of Advertised Volume Size for which we take the volume offline when the Allocated Volume Size reaches it. Default value is eqlGroupDefaultThinMaxGrow.

eqliscsiVolumeShrinkAutoAdjust.name: eqliscsiVolumeShrinkAutoAdjust
eqliscsiVolumeShrinkAutoAdjust.description: This field specifies whether snap-reserve should be adjusted automatically when shrinking or growing a volume. Default value is true. Example 1: If volume size is 1500MB, snap-reserve is 100%(1500MB) and snap-reserve used is 100%(1500MB), when shrinking volume to 750MB, snap-reserve will be automatically adjusted to 200%(1500MB) so that none of the snapshots will be lost. Example 2: If volume size is 1500MB, snap-reserve is 200%(3000MB) and snap-reserve used is 50%(750MB), when shrinking volume to 750MB, snap-reserve will be left at 200%(1500MB) even if auto adjust is set to true because the reserve 200%(1500MB) is greater than snap reserve used 750MB.

eqliscsiVolumeReplRollbackSeqNum.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplRollbackSeqNum
eqliscsiVolumeReplRollbackSeqNum.description: This field specifies the seq number of snap from which this volume was rolled back as part of demote or as part of replicaset rollback.

eqliscsiVolumeThinWarnMode.name: eqliscsiVolumeThinWarnMode
eqliscsiVolumeThinWarnMode.description: Specifies if the way Thin Provisioning feature will implement the Warning Threasholds. If 'warnWithOffline', the user will receive event warnings as they hit the Warning Threshold. When the user hits the MaxGrow Threshold, the volume will be taken offline. If 'warnWithIscsi', the user will recieve event warnings as they hit the Warning Threshold as well as an iSCSI WARNING on all writes that would cause a page allocation. When the user hits the MaxGrow Threshold, they will receive a Warning Event and an iSCSI WRITE ERROR on all writes that would have cause a page allocation. If 'warnWithOfflineForced' is set, this variable cannot be modified by an initiator. System will have the same behavior as warnWithOffline. This value has been deprecated. If 'warnWithSoftOnly' is set, the user will receive a check condtion when the volume passes the in-use warn limit. If 'warnWithHardOnly' is set, the user will receive no check condition when the volume passes the in-use warn limit, but the volume will reamain online once it passes the MaxGrow threshold.

eqliscsiVolumeFlags.name: eqliscsiVolumeFlags
eqliscsiVolumeFlags.description: This field defines the common place holder for Volume operational flags.

eqliscsiVolumeTemplate.name: eqliscsiVolumeTemplate
eqliscsiVolumeTemplate.description: This field specifies if the Volume is a Template Volume.

eqliscsiVolumeThinClone.name: eqliscsiVolumeThinClone
eqliscsiVolumeThinClone.description: This field specifies if the Volume is a Thin Clone Volume.

eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentMemberId.name: eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentMemberId
eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentMemberId.description: If the entry has indicated that this is a Thin Clone Volume, then this field will specify the Parent Index's MemberId.

eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentVolIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentVolIndex
eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentVolIndex.description: If the entry has indicated that this is a Thin Clone Volume, then this field will specify the Parent Index's VolumeIndex.

eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentPsvId.name: eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentPsvId
eqliscsiVolumeThinCloneParentPsvId.description: If non-empty, then this volume is a Thin Clone of a Template Volume. This field is the PsvId of the Template Volume.

eqliscsiVolumeAdminAccountKey.name: eqliscsiVolumeAdminAccountKey
eqliscsiVolumeAdminAccountKey.description: This field specifies the unique key for identifying a volume administrator that owns this volume. If no account has this value as its eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountKey, then the volume is unassigned.

eqliscsiVolumeSCSIQErr.name: eqliscsiVolumeSCSIQErr
eqliscsiVolumeSCSIQErr.description: This description is from T10/1799D sbc-3 rev 19. The following quote is from section 7.4.6 Control mode page. The queue error management (QERR) field specifies how the device server shall handle other tasks when one task is terminated with CHECK CONDITION status (see SAM-3). The task set type (see the TST field definition in this subclause) defines which other tasks are affected. If the TST field equals 000b, then all tasks from all I_T nexuses are affected. If the TST field equals 001b, then only tasks from the same I_T nexus as the task that is terminated with CHECK CONDITION status are affected. Note that the volume's QErr mask is kept in the lower 4 bits and all snapshots QErr mask is kept in the next 4 bits

eqliscsiVolumeBorrow.name: eqliscsiVolumeBorrow
eqliscsiVolumeBorrow.description: This field specifies if this Volume is allowed to borrow. All the volumes including replica sets created in V6.0.0 have this MIB variable set to 'enabled' although V6.0.0 doesn't support delegated space borrowing yet.

eqliscsiVolumeSectorSize.name: eqliscsiVolumeSectorSize
eqliscsiVolumeSectorSize.description: This field specifies, in bytes, the sector size of this volume.

eqliscsiSnapshotTable.name: eqliscsiSnapshotTable
eqliscsiSnapshotTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Volume Snap Shot Table TimeoutCreate:60 TimeoutDelete:60

eqliscsiSnapshotEntry.name: eqliscsiSnapshotEntry
eqliscsiSnapshotEntry.description: An entry (row) containing snap shot info.

eqliscsiSnapshotIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapshotIndex
eqliscsiSnapshotIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index which identifies a volume SnapShot.

eqliscsiSnapshotPsvId.name: eqliscsiSnapshotPsvId
eqliscsiSnapshotPsvId.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field contains an internal key for identifing a SnapShot.

eqliscsiSnapshotBasePsvId.name: eqliscsiSnapshotBasePsvId
eqliscsiSnapshotBasePsvId.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field contains an internal key which identifies the volume the SnapShot is associated with.

eqliscsiSnapshotName.name: eqliscsiSnapshotName
eqliscsiSnapshotName.description: This field specifies the friendly name used to identify a SnapShot. The name is auto-generated based on the volume name, though it can be overriden by the administrator.

eqliscsiSnapshotAccessType.name: eqliscsiSnapshotAccessType
eqliscsiSnapshotAccessType.description: This field specifies the access type for a SnapShot. The valid access types are read-write and read-only. The default access type is read-write.

eqliscsiSnapshotSize.name: eqliscsiSnapshotSize
eqliscsiSnapshotSize.description: This field specifies the amount of space in MB a SnapShot consumes. Note: Deleting the SnapShot is not guaranteed to return the space specified, since a single block can be associated with multiple SnapShots. This value is dynamic.

eqliscsiSnapshotAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiSnapshotAdminStatus
eqliscsiSnapshotAdminStatus.description: This field specifies whether a SnapShot is online or not. In order for an iSCSI initiator to access a snapshot it must be online. The default is offline.

eqliscsiSnapshotTimestamp.name: eqliscsiSnapshotTimestamp
eqliscsiSnapshotTimestamp.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies the creation time for volume. Time is represented as the time in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC, 1970-01-01.

eqliscsiSnapshotScheduleName.name: eqliscsiSnapshotScheduleName
eqliscsiSnapshotScheduleName.description: This field specifies the schedule used for SnapShots. The SnapShot schedule is configured independently and then applied to individual volumes. The default is no schedule is set.

eqliscsiSnapshotRollBack.name: eqliscsiSnapshotRollBack
eqliscsiSnapshotRollBack.description: This field specifies whether or not to roll a SnapShot back to a specified SnapShot. This shouldn't be a TruthValue, instead it should be the SnapShot number to roll back to. There is no default.

eqliscsiSnapshotTargetAlias.name: eqliscsiSnapshotTargetAlias
eqliscsiSnapshotTargetAlias.description: This field specifies what iSCSI alias will be used to identify the SnapShot. The alias is autogenerated by default, though it can be overriden.

eqliscsiSnapshotTargetIscsiName.name: eqliscsiSnapshotTargetIscsiName
eqliscsiSnapshotTargetIscsiName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies what iSCSI name will be used to identify the SnapShot. The name is autogenerated by default, though it can be overriden.

eqliscsiSnapshotScheduleIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapshotScheduleIndex
eqliscsiSnapshotScheduleIndex.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies the index of the snapshot policy if it is created by a snapshotpolicy, otherwise it will be set to zero. If the policy is deleted after the snapshot is created, this will be reset back to zero by the subsystem.

eqliscsiSnapshotDescription.name: eqliscsiSnapshotDescription
eqliscsiSnapshotDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that administrator can add to provide details about the snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapshotNodeIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapshotNodeIndex
eqliscsiSnapshotNodeIndex.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify this particular node within the ISCSI mibs. Instances of objects in those MIBS that are related to this iSCSI target will have this value of iscsiNodeIndex

eqliscsiSnapshotReplicated.name: eqliscsiSnapshotReplicated
eqliscsiSnapshotReplicated.description: When a row is created with this object set to a non zero value, and a replication relationship has been configured for the base volume, the snapshot will be queued to be replicated to the remote location indicated by the corresponing value of site index in the site table The value for this object cannot be changed to zero once the snapshot is created.

eqliscsiSnapshotType.name: eqliscsiSnapshotType
eqliscsiSnapshotType.description: Specifies the type of snapshot. Snapshot is of type of replica-site when the parent volume is of type replica-site.

eqliscsiSnapshotCollectionIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapshotCollectionIndex
eqliscsiSnapshotCollectionIndex.description: The eqliscsiSnapCollectionIndex if this snap is part of a group. Otherwise the value will be set to zero.

eqliscsiSnapshotStoragePoolIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapshotStoragePoolIndex
eqliscsiSnapshotStoragePoolIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying a storage pool.

eqliscsiSnapshotTargetLocalMemberId.name: eqliscsiSnapshotTargetLocalMemberId
eqliscsiSnapshotTargetLocalMemberId.description: This field specifies the first part of a unique index for identifing an iSCSI target.

eqliscsiSnapshotTargetIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapshotTargetIndex
eqliscsiSnapshotTargetIndex.description: This field specifies the second part of a unique index for identifing an iSCSI target.

eqliscsiSnapshotMultInitiator.name: eqliscsiSnapshotMultInitiator
eqliscsiSnapshotMultInitiator.description: Specifies if the access from multiple initiators is allowed for the snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapshotFlags.name: eqliscsiSnapshotFlags
eqliscsiSnapshotFlags.description: This field defines the common place holder for Snapshot operational flags. The flags must be of type enable(1) or disable(0), and the default will always be disable(0).

eqliscsiSnapshotCompressionDelay.name: eqliscsiSnapshotCompressionDelay
eqliscsiSnapshotCompressionDelay.description: The minimum amount of time (minutes) to wait before allowing this snapshot to be compressed.

eqliscsiSnapshotLifeExpectancy.name: eqliscsiSnapshotLifeExpectancy
eqliscsiSnapshotLifeExpectancy.description: The amount of time (minutes) this snapshot is estimated to be around.

eqliscsiVolumeMemberEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeMemberEntry
eqliscsiVolumeMemberEntry.description: An entry (row) containing volume member info.

eqliscsiVolumeMemberIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeMemberIndex
eqliscsiVolumeMemberIndex.description: This field specifies the index for the Member Volume table.

eqliscsiVolumeMemberPssId.name: eqliscsiVolumeMemberPssId
eqliscsiVolumeMemberPssId.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field contains the internal id for the Member which hosts a slice of the volume.

eqliscsiVolumeMemberShareOfVolume.name: eqliscsiVolumeMemberShareOfVolume
eqliscsiVolumeMemberShareOfVolume.description: This field contains storage allocated to the volume on the specified member. The storage is specified in MBs.

eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsTable
eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsTable.description: This table is used to gather information about the iSCSI Initiators connected to a specified volume.

eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsIndex
eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsIndex.description: This field specifies the index to the Volume Initiator table. The list is created from the iSCSI Initiators connected to a volume.

eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsName.name: eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsName
eqliscsiVolumeInitiatorsName.description: This field specifies the name of the iSCSI Initiator accessing this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEntry.description: An entry (row) containing snapshot scheduling policy information.The policy determines when to create snapshot(s) of a volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyIndex
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyIndex.description: This value uniquely identifies the snapshot policies for a volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyRowStatus.description: This value is used to manage the conceptual row.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyName.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyName
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyName.description: This value specifies user friendly name for the policy. It is unique within the context of a volume. Spaces are not allowed.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyAccessType.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyAccessType
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyAccessType.description: Snapshots created using this policy will have accesstype same as the value of this object.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStatus.description: Snapshots created using this policy will have status same as the value of this object.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyMaxKeep.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyMaxKeep
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyMaxKeep.description: The value of this object determines the maximum no of snapshots created by this policy that can exist at a given time. When number of snapshots created by this policy reaches this value, for creating a new snapshot oldest snapshot created using this policy will be deleted. In a set operation, if the new value of this object is less than the old value, required number of oldest snapshots created by this policy will be deleted.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyType.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyType
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyType.description: The value of this object determines the basic type of this policy. Except when set to once, the effective repetition period of the policy is determined using the value of this object along with the value of eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor. (See description of eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor for more information.)

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor.description: The value of this object along with eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyType determines the effective repetition interval for this policy. The valid values are PolicyType RepeatFactor once 1 hourly 1 daily 1-2147483647 weekly 1-2147483647 monthly 1-2147483647 If the policy type is daily and the value of this object is 2, snapshots will be taken once in every 2 days.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStartTime.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStartTime
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStartTime.description: The value of this object represents the time to start creating snapshot(s) within a day expressed as number of minutes from 12:00AM. The maximum value for this column is 24*60-1 which represents 11:59PM.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEndTime.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEndTime
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEndTime.description: The value of this object represents the time to stop creating snapshot(s) within a day expressed as number of minutes from 12:00AM. The maximum value for this column is 24*60-1 which represents 11:59PM. If eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyType is once, the value of this column doesn't have any significance. If the value of this column is greater than start time, it represents end-time on the same day as start time. If the value is less than or equal to start time, it represents end-time on the next day of start time. This value doesnt have significance when frequency is set to zero. Endtime is exclusive when calculating no of snapshots. Example: StartTime EndTime Frequency NoofSnapshots 1320(10pm) 1380(11pm) 30mins 2 1320(10pm) 240(4am) 60mins 6 1320(10pm) 1320(10pm) 60mins 24 1320(10pm) 1319(9:59pm) 60mins 24 1320(10pm) - 0mins 1

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyTimeFrequenc.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyTimeFrequency
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyTimeFrequenc.description: The value of this object determines how frequent snapshots must be taken between start time and end time. This value doesn't have significance when policy type is set to once. For other policytypes, the value of end time is exclusive. For example if starttime is 180 (3:00AM) and endtime is 240(4:00AM), when frequency is set to 30, snapshots will be created at 3:00AM, 3:30AM. If the value is zero, it represents invalid frequency and in such case, end time doesnt have significance.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStartDate.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStartDate
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyStartDate.description: The value of this object determines the date from which the policy will be active. By default, this is the policy creation date. The value is expressed as number of days since epoch.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEndDate.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEndDate
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyEndDate.description: The value of this object determines the date after which the policy will be inactive.It doesnt have significance when policy type is once. Default value is the mamixum value allowed. When set to maximum value, the policy will be active until it gets deleted. The value is expressed as number of days since epoch.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyWeekMask.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyWeekMask
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyWeekMask.description: The value of this column is significant only if policytype is set to weekly or monthly. When the value is 0x7fffffff, it represents a special meaning to the value of occurence. See the description for occurence below. The LSB to LSB+6 bits of the mask are significant. Each bit represents a day in the week with LSB being Mon and LSB+6 being Sun. If mask is 0x00000041 - snapshots will be created on Monday and Sunday. If mask is 0x0000007f - snapshots will be created on all weekdays which is effectively a daily policy. If mask is 0x0000001f, it represents week days.If mask is 0x00000060, it represents weekend days.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyMonthMask.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyMonthMask
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyMonthMask.description: The value of this column is currently not being used.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyNextCreate.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyNextCreate
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyNextCreate.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The value of this column represents number of seconds since epoch at which the next snapshot by this policy is going to be created.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyOccurence.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyOccurence
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyOccurence.description: The value of this column is significant only if the policy type is set to monthly. If weekmask is set to 0x7fffffff, the value of this column represents the occurence of a day with in a month. Example:If the value of this column is 5, it represents 5th day of the month. When the week mask is set to a value other than 0x7fffffff, the value of this column defines the occurence of a day as defined by weekmask. Example: When weekmask is set to 0x00000001 (Monday) and value of this column represents the following. Value Meaning 0x1 First monday of the month 0x2 Second monday of the month 0x3 Third monday of the month 0x4 Fourth monday of the month 0x7fffffff Last monday of the month

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyReplication.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyReplication
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyReplication.description: When a row is created with this object set to a non-zero value, and a replication relationship has been configured for the base volume, the snapshots created will be queued to be replicated to the remote location as defined by the corresponding entry in the site table. The value for this object cannot be changed once the schedule is created.

eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyAdminStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyAdminStatus.description: When disabled, the schedule will stop creating snapshots until re-enabled.

eqliscsiVolumeACLTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLTable
eqliscsiVolumeACLTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent-ReplicateOnCreate volume access table. This table contains a collection of volume access records. One table entry per access record. It is indexed by group id, volume, index and volume access record index. The number of entries equal to the number of volume access records specified by the user.

eqliscsiVolumeACLEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLEntry
eqliscsiVolumeACLEntry.description: An entry (row) containing volume access parameters to this target.

eqliscsiVolumeACLIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLIndex
eqliscsiVolumeACLIndex.description: The index value that uniquely identifies the volume access record.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorName.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorName
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorName.description: The name of iscsi initiator permitted to access the volume. If the name is an empty string or * then any initiator is allowed to access.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorIpAddress.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorIpAddress
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorIpAddress.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorAuthentication.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorAuthenticationMethod
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorAuthentication.description: The authentication method to be used for initiator authentication.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserName.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserName
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The user name to be used for initiator authentication if the authentication method is CHAP5 local or SRP local.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserPassword.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserPassword
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserPassword.description: The user name to be used for initiator authentication if the authentication method is CHAP5 local or SRP local

eqliscsiVolumeACLTargetType.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLTargetType
eqliscsiVolumeACLTargetType.description: The target type to be authenticated.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserName2.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserName2
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorUserName2.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The 256 byte character name user name to be used for initiator authentication if the authentication method is CHAP5 local or SRP local. This field supercedes the deprecated 128 byte field that performed the same function.

eqliscsiVolumeACLAuthType.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLAuthType
eqliscsiVolumeACLAuthType.description: The authentication type used. Currently it is set only by vds and should be left alone by the PSA firmware and non-vds PSA configuration tools.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorIpWildcard.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorIpWildcard
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorIpWildcard.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddressTyp.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddressType
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddressTyp.description: The ip address of the iscsi initiator permitted to access the volume in the form of x.x.x.number. If the number is zero then any ip address with the value from x.x.x.1 to x.x.x.255 is permitted to access the volume. If this variable is not set then any ip address will be permitted to access the volume.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddress.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddress
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddress.description: The ip address of the iscsi initiator permitted to access the volume in the form of x.x.x.number. If the number is zero then any ip address with the value from x.x.x.1 to x.x.x.255 is permitted to access the volume. If this variable is not set then any ip address will be permitted to access the volume.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetWildcardTy.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetWildcardType
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetWildcardTy.description: The wildcard mask defines which portion of eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddress that does not have to match for the initiator to be permitted access to the volume. The wildcard mask is expressed in the form x.x.x.x, where x is 255 or 0. When x is 255, then that portion of the initiator's ip address does have to match. When x is 0, then that portion of the initiator's ip address does not have to match the corresponding portion of eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddress. By default, the value of this variable is 255.255.255.255, which means the initiator's ip address must match exactly unless this variable is specified.

eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetWildcard.name: eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetWildcard
eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetWildcard.description: The wildcard mask defines which portion of eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddress that does not have to match for the initiator to be permitted access to the volume. The wildcard mask is expressed in the form x.x.x.x, where x is 255 or 0. When x is 255, then that portion of the initiator's ip address does have to match. When x is 0, then that portion of the initiator's ip address does not have to match the corresponding portion of eqliscsiVolumeACLInitiatorInetAddress. By default, the value of this variable is 255.255.255.255, which means the initiator's ip address must match exactly unless this variable is specified.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusTable
eqliscsiVolumeStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Storage Volume Table. This table contains a list of volumes in a group and their stats.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusPsvId.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusPsvId
eqliscsiVolumeStatusPsvId.description: This field is for internal use only.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusReservedSpace.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusReservedSpace
eqliscsiVolumeStatusReservedSpace.description: This field specifies how many MB of space is reserved for snapshots of this volume. This is a dynamic value, it is not Administrator setable.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusReservedSpaceAvail.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusReservedSpaceAvail
eqliscsiVolumeStatusReservedSpaceAvail.description: This field specifies how many MB of reserved space that is unused by the snapshots.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusActualMemberCount.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusActualMemberCount
eqliscsiVolumeStatusActualMemberCount.description: This field specifies the number of members this volume is spread across. It must be equal to number of rows in VolumeMemberTable for this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumSnapshots.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumSnapshots
eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumSnapshots.description: Indicates the number of snapshots that the system is maintaining on the specified volume

eqliscsiVolumeStatusCreationTime.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusCreationTime
eqliscsiVolumeStatusCreationTime.description: Indicates the local system time when the specified volume was created

eqliscsiVolumeStatusAvailable.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusAvailable
eqliscsiVolumeStatusAvailable.description: Indicates the local system time when the specified volume was created

eqliscsiVolumeStatusOperStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusOperStatus
eqliscsiVolumeStatusOperStatus.description: This field specifies the current operational status of the volume.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusConnections.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusConnections
eqliscsiVolumeStatusConnections.description: The value of this object represents number of active iscsi connections to this volume. It MUST match with the number of rows for this particular iscsiNode in iscsiConnectionAttributesTable.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusLostRaidBlocksAction.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusLostRaidBlocksAction
eqliscsiVolumeStatusLostRaidBlocksAction.description: This field specifies what action administrator wants to take on lost raid blocks.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumReplicas.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumReplicas
eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumReplicas.description: The value of this object represents the total number of replicas present for this volume across all replica sites. The value will match with the sum of values of eqliscsiVolumeReplNumReplicas that correspond to this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplReserveSpace.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplReserveSpace
eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplReserveSpace.description: The value of this object represents space reserved for this volume for replication purposes.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusAllocatedSpace.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusAllocatedSpace
eqliscsiVolumeStatusAllocatedSpace.description: The value of this object represents the actual materialized pages for this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplResvInUse.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplResvInUse
eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplResvInUse.description: This field represents the amount of local replication reserve in use.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplTxData.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplTxData
eqliscsiVolumeStatusReplTxData.description: This field represents the amount of data that will be transferred during next replication.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumOnlineSnaps.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumOnlineSnaps
eqliscsiVolumeStatusNumOnlineSnaps.description: This field represents the number of online snapshots on this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusPagesSharedWithParen.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusPagesSharedWithParent
eqliscsiVolumeStatusPagesSharedWithParen.description: This field represents the number of pages the volume shares with its parent. Is NA for a non-thin clone volume

eqliscsiVolumeStatusExternalConnections.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusExternalConnections
eqliscsiVolumeStatusExternalConnections.description: The value of this object represents number of active iscsi connections to this volume, not counting any extended copy sessions.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusSpaceBorrowing.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusSpaceBorrowing
eqliscsiVolumeStatusSpaceBorrowing.description: This field specifies how many MB of space that this volume is borrowing.

eqliscsiVolumeStatusBorrow.name: eqliscsiVolumeStatusBorrow
eqliscsiVolumeStatusBorrow.description: This field specifies operational status of borrowing.

eqliscsiSnapshotStatusTable.name: eqliscsiSnapshotStatusTable
eqliscsiSnapshotStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Storage Snapshot Table. This table contains a list of volumes in a group and their stats.

eqliscsiSnapshotStatusOperStatus.name: eqliscsiSnapshotStatusOperStatus
eqliscsiSnapshotStatusOperStatus.description: This field specifies the current operational status of the snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapshotStatusConnections.name: eqliscsiSnapshotStatusConnections
eqliscsiSnapshotStatusConnections.description: The value of this object represents number of active iscsi connections to this snapshot. It MUST match with the number of rows for this particular iscsiNode in iscsiConnectionAttributesTable.

eqliscsiSnapshotStatusLostRaidBlocksActi.name: eqliscsiSnapshotStatusLostRaidBlocksAction
eqliscsiSnapshotStatusLostRaidBlocksActi.description: This field specifies what action administrator wants to take on lost raid blocks.

eqliscsiLocalMemberId.name: eqliscsiLocalMemberId
eqliscsiLocalMemberId.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic A number which uniquely identifies this instance of the Equallogic SNMP agent within the group. This number will the same as the corresponding MemberIndex for this array in the eqlMemberTable.

eqliscsiLocalMemberIdLow.name: eqliscsiLocalMemberIdLow
eqliscsiLocalMemberIdLow.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic A number which uniquely identifies this instance of the Equallogic SNMP agent within the group. This number will the same as the corresponding MemberIndex for this array in the eqlMemberTable.

eqliscsiLocalMemberIdHigh.name: eqliscsiLocalMemberIdHigh
eqliscsiLocalMemberIdHigh.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic A number which uniquely identifies this instance of the Equallogic SNMP agent within the group. This number will the same as the corresponding MemberIndex for this array in the eqlMemberTable.

eqliscsiLastVolumeIndex.name: eqliscsiLastVolumeIndex
eqliscsiLastVolumeIndex.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic This object represents the highest numeric index that any row in the eqliscsiVolumeTable has. An application can use this value to determine an index with which to create an additional row in that table without scanning the entire table for a usable index.

eqliscsiVolumeIndexLow.name: eqliscsiVolumeIndexLow
eqliscsiVolumeIndexLow.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic This object represents the highest numeric index that any row in the eqliscsiVolumeTable has. An application can use this value to determine an index with which to create an additional row in that table without scanning the entire table for a usable index.

eqliscsiVolumeIndexHigh.name: eqliscsiVolumeIndexHigh
eqliscsiVolumeIndexHigh.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic This object represents the highest numeric index that any row in the eqliscsiVolumeTable has. An application can use this value to determine an index with which to create an additional row in that table without scanning the entire table for a usable index.

eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId0.name: eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId0
eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId0.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic first word of low volume PsvId

eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId1.name: eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId1
eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId1.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic second word of low volume PsvId

eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId2.name: eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId2
eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId2.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic third word of low volume PsvId

eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId3.name: eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId3
eqliscsiVolumeLowPsvId3.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic fourth word of low volume PsvId

eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId0.name: eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId0
eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId0.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic first word of high volume PsvId

eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId1.name: eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId1
eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId1.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic second word of high volume PsvId

eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId2.name: eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId2
eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId2.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic third word of high volume PsvId

eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId3.name: eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId3
eqliscsiVolumeHighPsvId3.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic fourth word of high volume PsvId

eqliscsiLastSnapshotIndex.name: eqliscsiLastSnapshotIndex
eqliscsiLastSnapshotIndex.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic This object represents the highest numeric index that any row in the eqliscsiSnapshotTable has. An application can use this value to determine an index with which to create an additional row in that table without scanning the entire table for a usable index.

eqliscsiLastTargetIndex.name: eqliscsiLastTargetIndex
eqliscsiLastTargetIndex.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic This object represents the highest numeric index that any row in the eqliscsiTargetTable has. An application can use this value to determine an index with which to create an additional row in that table without scanning the entire table for a usable index.

eqliscsiNodeTable.name: eqliscsiNodeTable
eqliscsiNodeTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic iscsi Node Table: maintains a mapping of the iscsi Node indeces back to the eql private volume and snapshot Mibs

eqliscsiNodeEntry.name: eqliscsiNodeEntry
eqliscsiNodeEntry.description: An entry containing the aformentioned mapping. The value of eqliscsiSnapshotIndex will be zero (0) for those nodes that represent volumes rather than snapshots.

eqliscsiNodeIndex.name: eqliscsiNodeIndex
eqliscsiNodeIndex.description: The node index of the iSCSI target node. This will correspond to a value of iscsiNodeIndex, eqliscsiVOlumeNodeIndex, or eqliscsiSnapshotIndex. The indeces are allocated such that even values of this object repesent snapshots and odd values represent volumes.

eqliscsiNodeLocalMemberId.name: eqliscsiNodeLocalMemberId
eqliscsiNodeLocalMemberId.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic A number which uniquely identifies this instance of the Equallogic SNMP agent within the group. This number will the same as the corresponding MemberIndex for this array in the eqlMemberTable.

eqliscsiNodeVolumeIndex.name: eqliscsiNodeVolumeIndex
eqliscsiNodeVolumeIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing a volume in the eqliscsiVolumeTable. An instance here will reflect a specific instance in the eqliscsiVolumeTable and/or eqliscsiSnapshotTable.

eqliscsiNodeSnapshotIndex.name: eqliscsiNodeSnapshotIndex
eqliscsiNodeSnapshotIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index which identifies a volume SnapShot. in the eqliscsiSnapshotTable. If the conceptiual row in this table does NOT reflect a snapshot, this instance of the variable will be set to zero (0).

eqliscsiVolumeAuthAttributesTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeAuthAttributesTable
eqliscsiVolumeAuthAttributesTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent A list of identities that the PSA uses to authenticate itself to initiators

eqliscsiVolumeAuthAttributesEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeAuthAttributesEntry
eqliscsiVolumeAuthAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular target node's authorized initiator identity.

eqliscsiVolumeAuthIdentity.name: eqliscsiVolumeAuthIdentity
eqliscsiVolumeAuthIdentity.description: A pointer to the corresponding IPS-AUTH MIB ipsAuthCredChapAttributesEntry that contains the chap credentials which this volume will use to authenticate itself to initiators requiring CHAP authentication

eqliscsiVolumeBindingTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeBindingTable
eqliscsiVolumeBindingTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent A table that specifies the specific members of the group that a particular volume may occupy

eqliscsiVolumeBindingEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeBindingEntry
eqliscsiVolumeBindingEntry.description: An entry (row) containing a reference to a specific volume and a specific member where that volume's pages can exist.If no entry exists for a particular volume, the member page allocation will be determined by the system.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteIndex
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteIndex.description: A unique 32 bit identifier for this row

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteName.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteName
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteName.description: A concise, human readable string indentifier for the site, for example: Boston HQ

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteIpAddr.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteIpAddr
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteIpAddr.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteControlCredentials.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteControlCredentials
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteControlCredentials.description: A pointer to the corresponding IPS-AUTH MIB ipsAuthCredChapAttributesEntry that contains the chap credentials which this PSA will use to authenticate itself to replica targets for management requiring operations.

eqliscsiVolumeReplControlTargetIscsiName.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplControlTargetIscsiName
eqliscsiVolumeReplControlTargetIscsiName.description: The iSCSI name of the group-wide target that is used to encapsulate replication control commands.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSNMPContext.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSNMPContext
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSNMPContext.description: The SNMP context that will be used by applications at the local site to browse MIBs on the remote site.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteContact.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteContact
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteContact.description: This field contains the full name of the replication site administrator.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteEmail.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteEmail
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteEmail.description: This field specifies the email address of the replication site administrator.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSitePhone.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSitePhone
eqliscsiVolumeReplSitePhone.description: This field specifies the phone number of the replication site administrator.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteMobile.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteMobile
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteMobile.description: This field specifies the cell phone number of the replication site administrator.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteDescription.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteDescription
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteDescription.description: This field contains a detailed description of the site.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceAllocated.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceAllocated
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceAllocated.description: The total amount of pool space reserved for use by the site. Replication may be set up as needed by the administrators at the site as long as the total required reserve does not exceed this value.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceUsed.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceUsed
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceUsed.description: The amount of reserve space already used by replicated volumes configured by the site administrator. This value may not exceed the corresponding value for eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceAllocated

eqliscsiVolumeReplControlChannelStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplControlChannelStatus
eqliscsiVolumeReplControlChannelStatus.description: The current status of the control channel to replica site.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminStatus
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminStatus.description: When set to pause, all the replications going to this replica site will be temporarily suspended until set by the user to start.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteTotalNumSnapshots.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteTotalNumSnapshots
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteTotalNumSnapshots.description: the total number of snapshots in secondary site

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceSubscribed.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceSubscribed
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteSpaceSubscribed.description: The total amount of pool space subscribed for use by the site. Subscribed space is the advertised space for thin provisioned volumes. For classic volumes, subscribed space is the volume size.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteInetAddrType.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteInetAddrType
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteInetAddrType.description: The well-known IP address of the group located at the site. This will be the IP address to which iSCSI replication traffic will be directed.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteInetAddr.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteInetAddr
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteInetAddr.description: The well-known IP address of the group located at the site. This will be the IP address to which iSCSI replication traffic will be directed.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteNASPartnershipId.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteNASPartnershipId
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteNASPartnershipId.description: The NAS replication PartnershipId. This partnershipId is Exastore way to keep track of a NAS partnership. If NAS replication is configured This will be a non-zero Id. 0 will be used when NAS replication is not configured on this partnership.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteBlockState.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteBlockState
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteBlockState.description: The state of this site for block replication.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteNASState.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteNASState
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteNASState.description: The state of this site for NAS replication.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteType.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteType
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteType.description: This field represents the site type. 0 is normal aka regular repl site. 1 is external site that is not an EQL array.

eqliscsiVolumeReplAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplAdminStatus
eqliscsiVolumeReplAdminStatus.description: This object is used to request a change in the current admin status of the replication process. When read, it represents the current admin status. If disabled, the replication can NEVER be restarted again.

eqliscsiVolumeReplRemoteIscsiName.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplRemoteIscsiName
eqliscsiVolumeReplRemoteIscsiName.description: This field specifies the iSCSI target name for the remote volume which serves as a replica target.

eqliscsiVolumeReplRemoteIscsiPort.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplRemoteIscsiPort
eqliscsiVolumeReplRemoteIscsiPort.description: This field specifies the Internet Portocol port number for the iSCSI target specified in the corresponding instance of eqliscsiVolumeReplRemoteIscsiName. The target will be accessed using this port.

eqliscsiVolumeReplRemotePsvId.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplRemotePsvId
eqliscsiVolumeReplRemotePsvId.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY A 16 byte, universally unique identifier for the remote replica volume. The value for this object is determined by the array where the replica set is located.

eqliscsiVolumeReplDiscardPolicy.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplDiscardPolicy
eqliscsiVolumeReplDiscardPolicy.description: In the event that the replication process cannot complete the transfer of the volume to the replica site, the action taken on the incomplete replica is one of these: 1) overrun - complete the in progress replica 2) discard - destry the in progress replica and restart a new one

eqliscsiVolumeReplReserve.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplReserve
eqliscsiVolumeReplReserve.description: This value represents the percentage of space reserved for replication at remote site. The value effectively determines the maximum number of replicas that can be maintained at the remote site. The default value is good for maintaining one replica.

eqliscsiVolumeReplDeletionPolicy.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplDeletionPolicy
eqliscsiVolumeReplDeletionPolicy.description: The depth of deletion desired when replication at the local array is disabled for an associated primary volume. The choices are as follows: local_only: Only the local references to the remote replica sets will be removed. The remote replica sets will remain intact and will need to be managed at the remote site. remote: The remote replica sets will be deleted. This will destroy all of the remote data. Note that setting the value to 'remote' will cause the delete operation to fail if there is no connectivity to the remote site. If the deletion needs to proceed regardless of the state of the remote site, the local_only policy shoud be used

eqliscsiVolumeReplNumReplicas.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplNumReplicas
eqliscsiVolumeReplNumReplicas.description: The number of replicas present at the replica site for this volume. The value of this object matches with number of rows in eqliscsiRemoteReplicaTable that correspond to this replication entry.

eqliscsiVolumeReplPrimaryReserve.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplPrimaryReserve
eqliscsiVolumeReplPrimaryReserve.description: The space reserved on the primary site to keep track of changes occurred between replications. The value is represented as percentage of actual volume size. It is recommended to keep this value 100 if fast fail-back is not enabled. If the value is less than 100, replication will fail if the space is not sufficient to keep track of the changes. It is recommended to keep this value 200 if fast fail-back is enabled.

eqliscsiVolumeReplPrimaryBorrow.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplPrimaryBorrow
eqliscsiVolumeReplPrimaryBorrow.description: When the space reserved for replication is not sufficient to keep track of volume changes, space will be borrowed from free space if the value of this object is true. Space will not be borrowed when the value is false. Setting this variable to true doesn't gaurantee replication to succeed as there may be no free space available to borrow. The borrwed space is returned back to the pool after the replication is complete.

eqliscsiVolumeReplManualReplStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplManualReplStatus
eqliscsiVolumeReplManualReplStatus.description: Enabling manual replication will allow the replica snaps on the primary and secondary groups to be visible to iscsi clients. When user connects to primary repl snap and finishes the data transfer, user can set it do done. The done state will be set to disabled after secondary site admin finishes the data transfer on secondary site and indicates done on secondary site.

eqliscsiVolumeReplCurLwMark.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplCurLwMark
eqliscsiVolumeReplCurLwMark.description: This field specifies the smallest volume size in MB since the last replication that this volume has been shrunk down to. This is used to track volumes shrinking and then growing so that the secondary side knows to release the pages when the volume is replicated. Note: Volume size is round to a multiple of 15MB.

eqliscsiVolumeReplLwMark.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplLwMark
eqliscsiVolumeReplLwMark.description: This field is eqliscsiVolumeCurLwMark for the current replication started. This is used to track volumes shrinking and then growing so that the secondary side knows to release the pages when the volume is replicated. Note: Volume size is round to a multiple of 15MB.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSize.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSize
eqliscsiVolumeReplSize.description: This field is eqliscsiVolumeSize for the current replication started.

eqliscsiVolumeReplThinProvision.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplThinProvision
eqliscsiVolumeReplThinProvision.description: This field is eqliscsiVolumeThinProvision for the current replication started.

eqliscsiVolumeReplMinThinReserve.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplMinThinReserve
eqliscsiVolumeReplMinThinReserve.description: This field is eqliscsiVolumeMinThinReserve for the current replication started.

eqliscsiVolumeReplThinWarnPercentage.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplThinWarnPercentage
eqliscsiVolumeReplThinWarnPercentage.description: This field is eqliscsiVolumeThinWarnPercentage for the current replication started.

eqliscsiVolumeReplThinMaxGrowPercentage.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplThinMaxGrowPercentage
eqliscsiVolumeReplThinMaxGrowPercentage.description: This field is eqliscsiVolumeThinMaxGrowPercentage for the current replication started.

eqliscsiVolumeReplDynamicThinReserve.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplDynamicThinReserve
eqliscsiVolumeReplDynamicThinReserve.description: This field is eqliscsiVolumeDynamicThinReserve for the current replication started.

eqliscsiVolumeReplFailBackMode.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplFailBackMode
eqliscsiVolumeReplFailBackMode.description: This field specifies whether fast fail-back is enabled for this replication or not. By default fail-back will operate in regular mode. If user enables fast fail-back mode, primary site needs to keep the last successful replication snap ie fail-back snap. When customers upgrade to 3.2, the existing volumes will operate in regular fail-back mode.

eqliscsiVolumeReplPromoteSeqNum.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplPromoteSeqNum
eqliscsiVolumeReplPromoteSeqNum.description: This field specifies whether this replicaset was demoted to failback replicaset and later promoted. This value will be set to non-zero if during promote we couldn't communicating to the remote site. The value will be the sequence number on the volume during the promote.

eqliscsiVolumeReplTemplateReplicated.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplTemplateReplicated
eqliscsiVolumeReplTemplateReplicated.description: This field specifies if the Template has been successfully replicated

eqliscsiVolumeReplSyncAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSyncAdminStatus
eqliscsiVolumeReplSyncAdminStatus.description: Enabling sync replication will allow the replica volume to become online at the end of first successful replication. The changes to volume on primary will be comitted to the replica volume on secondary synchronously. When the AdminStatus is set to disabled the replica volume on the secondary will be brought offline.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSyncOperStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSyncOperStatus
eqliscsiVolumeReplSyncOperStatus.description: When SyncAdminStatus is enabled the OperStatus indicates the state of sync replication. The replica volume on the secondary is brought online at the end of the first successful replication. The sync repl will then start xfering data to the replica volume. The states waiting-for-first-sync and first-sync-done indicate the SyncRepl operating states.

eqliscsiVolumeReplThinClone.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplThinClone
eqliscsiVolumeReplThinClone.description: This field specifies if the Volume is a Thin Clone Volume.

eqliscsiVolumeReplOperStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplOperStatus
eqliscsiVolumeReplOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the replication process.

eqliscsiVolumeReplMBRemaining.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplMBRemaining
eqliscsiVolumeReplMBRemaining.description: If a transfer of replica data is in progress, the count of MB successfully transferred to the replica site will be here. If no transfer is in progress, this object will read zero (0).

eqliscsiVolumeReplMBCompleted.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplMBCompleted
eqliscsiVolumeReplMBCompleted.description: If a transfer of replica data is in progress, the count of MB remaining to be transferred to the replica site will be here. If no transfer is in progress, this object will read zero (0).

eqliscsiVolumeReplCurrentSnapshot.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplCurrentSnapshot
eqliscsiVolumeReplCurrentSnapshot.description: The value of this represents the instance of the snapshot in eqliscsiSnapshotTable that is currently being replicated. If there is no replication in progress, the value will be set to NULL.

eqliscsiVolumeReplCancel.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplCancel
eqliscsiVolumeReplCancel.description: Setting this variable to true will cause cancellation of any replication that is in progress.

eqliscsiVolumeRemoteReplReserveIncrNeede.name: eqliscsiVolumeRemoteReplReserveIncrNeeded
eqliscsiVolumeRemoteReplReserveIncrNeede.description: In percentage. remote replica reserve needs to be increased by this value for replication to the partner to continue. Valid only in remoteReplReserveLow and remoteReplReserveInvalid states.

eqliscsiVolumeReplFailbackSnap.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplFailbackSnap
eqliscsiVolumeReplFailbackSnap.description: This pointer points to the fast fail-back snap kept in the local replication reserve.

eqliscsiRemoteVolumeIndex.name: eqliscsiRemoteVolumeIndex
eqliscsiRemoteVolumeIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing a remote volume. The index is the same as the value for eqliscsiVolumeIndex on the remote site.

eqliscsiRemoteSnapIndex.name: eqliscsiRemoteSnapIndex
eqliscsiRemoteSnapIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing a snapshot. The index is the same as the value for eqliscsiSnapshotIndex on the remote site.

eqliscsiRemoteReplName.name: eqliscsiRemoteReplName
eqliscsiRemoteReplName.description: This field specifies the friendly name used to identify the replica. The name is auto-generated. The name is unique between replicas of a single volume at a particular site.

eqliscsiRemoteReplISCSIName.name: eqliscsiRemoteReplISCSIName
eqliscsiRemoteReplISCSIName.description: The iscsi name of the volume for which this site is keeping replicas.

eqliscsiRemoteReplPsvId.name: eqliscsiRemoteReplPsvId
eqliscsiRemoteReplPsvId.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY A universally unique 16 byte identifier for the remote replica.

eqliscsiRemoteReplAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiRemoteReplAdminStatus
eqliscsiRemoteReplAdminStatus.description: Manage the replica status. The row will be deleted from this table if value is set to delete. Status will be in-progress if this replica is currently getting replicated to the secondary site. The replica will be set to incomplete if the replication is disabled.

eqliscsiRemoteReplTimeStamp.name: eqliscsiRemoteReplTimeStamp
eqliscsiRemoteReplTimeStamp.description: This field specifies the creation time of the replica. Time is represented as the time in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC, 1970-01-01.

eqliscsiRemoteReplSnapColIndex.name: eqliscsiRemoteReplSnapColIndex
eqliscsiRemoteReplSnapColIndex.description: This field specifies the index of the snap collection at remote site if this replica is part of a collection. Otherwise value will be zero.

eqliscsiRemoteReplScheduleIndex.name: eqliscsiRemoteReplScheduleIndex
eqliscsiRemoteReplScheduleIndex.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies the index of the schedule on the primary site that initiated create replica operation ie eqliscsiVolumeSnapshotPolicyIndex . If this replica is not directly created by a schedule, but created as part of replica collection creation and the replica collection is created by a schedule, the value of this field will still be set to index of the replica collection schedule. ie eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyIndex. This will be reset to zero when schedule is deleted.

eqliscsiRemoteReplLocalMemberId.name: eqliscsiRemoteReplLocalMemberId
eqliscsiRemoteReplLocalMemberId.description: This field represents eqliscsiLocalMemberId field of the snapshot index of the replica on secondary site.

eqliscsiReplicaSetEntry.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetEntry
eqliscsiReplicaSetEntry.description: The Replica set consists of the base volume and the snapshots associated with this base volume.

eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryIscsiName.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryIscsiName
eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryIscsiName.description: The iscsi name of the volume for which this site is keeping replicas.

eqliscsiReplicaSetReserve.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetReserve
eqliscsiReplicaSetReserve.description: The value of this object specifies how much percentage of space reserved for replication. This value matches with correspoding eqliscsiVolumeReplReserve value on the primary site. The value is initialized and maintained by the control channel.

eqliscsiReplicaSetSite.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetSite
eqliscsiReplicaSetSite.description: Represents the value of eqliscsiReplicantSiteIndex that corresponds to the site to which this replica belongs.

eqliscsiReplicaSetAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetAdminStatus
eqliscsiReplicaSetAdminStatus.description: This object is used to request a change in the current admin status of the replication process. When read, it represents the current admin status.

eqliscsiReplicaSetPromotePolicy.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetPromotePolicy
eqliscsiReplicaSetPromotePolicy.description: This object represents the policy that is implemented when the replica set is promoted to a conventional volume. If the value of this object is set to 1, the iscsi name of the target is generated uniquely using conventional rules. When set to 2, the target assumes the iscsi name of the primary volume. In this case, that name will be the same as the value for this instance of eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryIscsiName.

eqliscsiReplicaSetManualReplStatus.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetManualReplStatus
eqliscsiReplicaSetManualReplStatus.description: This object is used to let the secondary know that the transfer of data has completed for volumes using manual data transfer for replication.

eqliscsiReplicaSetFailBackMode.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetFailBackMode
eqliscsiReplicaSetFailBackMode.description: This field specifies the mode of fail-back. In a normal fail-back mode, to get primary site back in sync with secondary site volume, all the volume contents must be transferred back to primary site. In fast fail-back mode, only the changes since last successful replication will be sent back to primary site. primary site needs to keep the last successful replication snap ie fail-back snap. When customers upgrade to 3.2, the existing volumes will operate in normal fail-back mode.SNMP managers cannot set this field. The value of this field gets configured when the primary site field eqliscsiVolumeReplFailBackMode gets configured.

eqliscsiReplicaSetType.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetType
eqliscsiReplicaSetType.description: This field specifies whether the replicaset is a regular replicaset or a fail-back replicaset. A regular replicaset is created on secondary site by the system when user enables replication of a volume on the primary site. A replicated-primary volume on the primary site can be demoted as a fail-back replicaset. A regular volume cannot be demoted as fail-back replicaset. Fail-back replicasets will have the volume configuration, ACL records, schedules etc before the demote, but that configuration will not be active. Fail-back replicasets can later be promoted as a replicated-primary volume when the volume is ready to resume its role.

eqliscsiReplicaSetAccess.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetAccess
eqliscsiReplicaSetAccess.description: By default, replicasets provide no-access to the user ie users cannot access the replicas or replicaset from an initiator. read-only-replicas provide read-only access to the replicas as well as the replicaset. Users must be able to connect to the replicas and replicaset using iscsi target names. Note that in-progress replica will not be available to read until the replication finishes.

eqliscsiReplicaSetFailbackReserve.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetFailbackReserve
eqliscsiReplicaSetFailbackReserve.description: The value local repl reserve before demoting outbound-replicaset to failback-replicaset

eqliscsiReplicaSetLSRPsvId.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetLSRPsvId
eqliscsiReplicaSetLSRPsvId.description: If non-zero, the value represents the PsvId of last successful replication snapshot of this replicaset. This value will only be set when promoting a replicaset as failover volume.The value will be reset after failover volume is demoted as inbound replicaset and first replica is created.

eqliscsiReplicaSetOrigSize.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetOrigSize
eqliscsiReplicaSetOrigSize.description: The value of this column represents the size of the recovery volume when it was promoted.

eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryMemberId.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryMemberId
eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryMemberId.description: The value of this column represents the eqliscsiLocalMemberId of the corresponding volume on the primary site.

eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryVolumeIndex.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryVolumeIndex
eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimaryVolumeIndex.description: The value of this column represents the eqliscsiVolumeIndex of the corresponding volume on the primary site.

eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimarySite.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimarySite
eqliscsiReplicaSetPrimarySite.description: The value of this column represents the eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteIndex of the corresponding volume on the primary site.

eqliscsiReplicaSetTemplateReplicated.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetTemplateReplicated
eqliscsiReplicaSetTemplateReplicated.description: This field specifies if the Template set has been successfully replicated

eqliscsiReplicaSetSyncAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetSyncAdminStatus
eqliscsiReplicaSetSyncAdminStatus.description: This field is there to let the secondary know when to bring the secondary replica volume online or offline. The replica volume will be brought online when syncRep is enabled and it will be brought offline when syncRep is disabled.

eqliscsiReplicaSetThinClone.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetThinClone
eqliscsiReplicaSetThinClone.description: This field specifies if the Volume is a Thin Clone Volume.

eqliscsiReplicaSetRemotePsvId.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetRemotePsvId
eqliscsiReplicaSetRemotePsvId.description: A 16 byte, universally unique identifier for the remote replicated volume. The value for this object is specified by the array where the volume is located.

eqliscsiReplicaSetStatusTable.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetStatusTable
eqliscsiReplicaSetStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic replica set status Table. This table contains a list of replicasets with their size, status etc.

eqliscsiReplicaSetOperStatus.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetOperStatus
eqliscsiReplicaSetOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the replication process.

eqliscsiReplicaSetSize.name: eqliscsiReplicaSetSize
eqliscsiReplicaSetSize.description: The size of the replicaset in MegaBytes.This includes the local replication reserve for failback replicasets.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteTable.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteTable
eqliscsiReplicantSiteTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent The replicant site table contains all of the remote sites which have been given access to the local storage pool for the purposes of creating replica sets.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteIndex.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteIndex
eqliscsiReplicantSiteIndex.description: A unique 32 bit identifier for this row

eqliscsiReplicantSiteName.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteName
eqliscsiReplicantSiteName.description: A concise, human readable string indentifier for the site, for example: Boston HQ

eqliscsiReplicantSiteIpAddr.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteIpAddr
eqliscsiReplicantSiteIpAddr.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteControlCredentials.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteControlCredentials
eqliscsiReplicantSiteControlCredentials.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY A pointer to the corresponding IPS-AUTH MIB ipsAuthCredChapAttributesEntry that contains the chap credentials which this PSA will use to authenticate itself to primary sites.

eqliscsiReplicantControlTargetIscsiName.name: eqliscsiReplicantControlTargetIscsiName
eqliscsiReplicantControlTargetIscsiName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The iSCSI name of the group-wide target that is used to encapsulate replication control commands.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteSNMPContext.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteSNMPContext
eqliscsiReplicantSiteSNMPContext.description: The SNMP context that will be used by applications at the local site to browse MIBs on the remote site.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteContact.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteContact
eqliscsiReplicantSiteContact.description: This field contains the full name of the replication site administrator.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteEmail.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteEmail
eqliscsiReplicantSiteEmail.description: This field specifies the email address of the replication site administrator.

eqliscsiReplicantSitePhone.name: eqliscsiReplicantSitePhone
eqliscsiReplicantSitePhone.description: This field specifies the phone number of the replication site administrator.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteMobile.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteMobile
eqliscsiReplicantSiteMobile.description: This field specifies the cell phone number of the replication site administrator.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteDescription.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteDescription
eqliscsiReplicantSiteDescription.description: This field contains a detailed description of the site.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceAllocated.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceAllocated
