eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceAllocated.description: The total amount of pool space reserved for use by the site. Replication may be set up as needed by the administrators at the site as long as the total required reserve does not exceed this value.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceUsed.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceUsed
eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceUsed.description: The amount of reserve space already used by replicated volumes configured by the site administrator. This value may not exceed the corresponding value for eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceAllocated

eqliscsiReplicantSiteControlChannelStatu.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteControlChannelStatus
eqliscsiReplicantSiteControlChannelStatu.description: The current status of the control channel from primary site.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteAdminStatus
eqliscsiReplicantSiteAdminStatus.description: When set to pause, all the replications coming from this primary site will be temporarily suspended until set by the user to enabled. When set to nuke, all replicasets will be deleted.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteTotalNumSnapshots.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteTotalNumSnapshots
eqliscsiReplicantSiteTotalNumSnapshots.description: the total number of snapshots in secondary site.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteStoragePoolIndex.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteStoragePoolIndex
eqliscsiReplicantSiteStoragePoolIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying a storage pool.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceSubscribed.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceSubscribed
eqliscsiReplicantSiteSpaceSubscribed.description: The total amount of pool space subscribed for use by the site. Subscribed space is the advertised space for thin provisioned volumes and it is the actual volume size for regular volumes.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteInetAddrType.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteInetAddrType
eqliscsiReplicantSiteInetAddrType.description: The well-known IP address of the group located at the site. This will be the IP address to which iSCSI replication traffic will be directed.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteInetAddr.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteInetAddr
eqliscsiReplicantSiteInetAddr.description: The well-known IP address of the group located at the site. This will be the IP address to which iSCSI replication traffic will be directed.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteUnmanagedSpace.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteUnmanagedSpace
eqliscsiReplicantSiteUnmanagedSpace.description: The total amount of pool space not managed by the site. This includes the space used by the unmanaged replica sets and recovery volumes.

eqliscsiReplicantSiteReplType.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteReplType
eqliscsiReplicantSiteReplType.description: This field represents the site type. 0 is normal aka regular repl site. 1 is external site that is not EQL.

eqliscsiVolCollectionObjectsTable.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionObjectsTable
eqliscsiVolCollectionObjectsTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains the list of volume objects in each collection.

eqliscsiVolCollectionIndex.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionIndex
eqliscsiVolCollectionIndex.description: A unique 32 bit identifier for this row

eqliscsiVolCollectionObjectRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionObjectRowStatus
eqliscsiVolCollectionObjectRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row.

eqliscsiVolCollectionTable.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionTable
eqliscsiVolCollectionTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains the list of volume collections and the supported operations on the collection.

eqliscsiVolCollectionRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionRowStatus
eqliscsiVolCollectionRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row. When deleteing a row from this table all the corresponding rows in snapcollection table must be reset to zero vol collection index

eqliscsiVolCollectionName.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionName
eqliscsiVolCollectionName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies a user friendly name for this collection. The name must be unique within a group. The name must not contain spaces or special characters. The name can be up to 64 characters in length. There is no default.

eqliscsiVolCollectionDescription.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionDescription
eqliscsiVolCollectionDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details about this collection. The description can be up to 128 characters.

eqliscsiVolCollectionReplService.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionReplService
eqliscsiVolCollectionReplService.description: This field specifies the replication service on the volume collection. If this volume collection is created for replication of a volume collection at partner site, then the value is set to replica-site. If this volume collection is enabled for replication to a partner site, the the value is set to replicated-primary.

eqliscsiVolCollectionSite.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSite
eqliscsiVolCollectionSite.description: This field specifies the partner to which this collection belongs. The value will match with eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteIndex if this collection belongs to a partner. Otherwise the value is set to zero. The value will be non-zero only when eqliscsiVolCollectionReplService is replica-site.

eqliscsiVolCollectionFlags.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionFlags
eqliscsiVolCollectionFlags.description: This fields defines the common place holder for volume collection operational flags. The flags must be of type enable(1) or disable(0), and the default will always be disable(0).

eqliscsiSnapCollectionObjectsTable.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionObjectsTable
eqliscsiSnapCollectionObjectsTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains the list of snapshot objects in each collection.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionIndex
eqliscsiSnapCollectionIndex.description: A unique 32 bit identifier for this row

eqliscsiSnapCollectionObjectRowStatus.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionObjectRowStatus
eqliscsiSnapCollectionObjectRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row. Rowstatus is set to notInService by the subsystem when the actual snapshot represented by this row is deleted. The row from this table will be automatically deleted when the corresponding volume is deleted (or) #when all rows of this group have the status notInService# (or) when the corresponding row is deleted from snapcollection table.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionTable.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionTable
eqliscsiSnapCollectionTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains the list of snapshot collections and the supported operations on the collection. TimeoutCreate:60 TimeoutDelete:60

eqliscsiSnapCollectionRowStatus.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionRowStatus
eqliscsiSnapCollectionRowStatus.description: Row status used to manage this row.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionName.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionName
eqliscsiSnapCollectionName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies a user friendly name for this collection. The name must not contain spaces or special characters. The name can be up to 64 characters in length. There is no default.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionDescription.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionDescription
eqliscsiSnapCollectionDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details about this collection. The description can be up to 128 characters.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionTimestamp.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionTimestamp
eqliscsiSnapCollectionTimestamp.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies the creation time for snapshot. Time is represented as the time in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC, 1970-01-01.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionNoofSnaps.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionNoofSnaps
eqliscsiSnapCollectionNoofSnaps.description: No of snapshots in this collection at the time of creation.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionVolIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionVolIndex
eqliscsiSnapCollectionVolIndex.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The index of the volcollection that created this group. When the volcollection is deleted, this value will be set to zero.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionVSS.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionVSS
eqliscsiSnapCollectionVSS.description: If this snap collection is created using vss.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionScheduleIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionScheduleIndex
eqliscsiSnapCollectionScheduleIndex.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies the index of the snapshot policy if it is created by a snapshotpolicy, otherwise it will be set to zero. If the policy is deleted after the snapshot is created, this will be reset back to zero by the subsystem.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionReplicated.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionReplicated
eqliscsiSnapCollectionReplicated.description: When a row is created with this object set to a non zero value, , the snapcollection will be queued to be replicated to the remote location indicated by the corresponing value of site index in the site table The value for this object cannot be changed to zero once the snapcollection is created.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionSite.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionSite
eqliscsiSnapCollectionSite.description: If non-zero, this value represents the partner who created this snap collection ie eqliscsiReplicantSiteIndex. This collection belongs to that partner not to our group.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEntry.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEntry
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEntry.description: An entry (row) containing snapshot scheduling policy information.The policy determines when to create snapshot(s) of a volume collection.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyIndex.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyIndex
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyIndex.description: This value uniquely identifies the snapshot policies for a volume collection.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyRowStatus.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyRowStatus
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyRowStatus.description: This value is used to manage the conceptual row.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyName.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyName
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyName.description: This value specifies user friendly name for the policy. It is unique within the context of a volume collection. Spaces are not allowed.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyAccessType.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyAccessType
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyAccessType.description: Snapshots created using this policy will have accesstype same as the value of this object.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStatus.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStatus
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStatus.description: Snapshots created using this policy will have status same as the value of this object.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyMaxKeep.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyMaxKeep
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyMaxKeep.description: The value of this object determines the maximum no of snapshots created by this policy that can exist at a given time. When number of snapshots created by this policy reaches this value, for creating a new snapshot oldest snapshot created using this policy will be deleted. In a set operation, if the new value of this object is less than the old value, required number of oldest snapshots created by this policy will be deleted.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyType.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyType
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyType.description: The value of this object determines the basic type of this policy. Except when set to once, the effective repetition period of the policy is determined using the value of this object along with the value of eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyRepeatFactor. (See description of eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyRepeatFactor for more information.)

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyRepeatFactor.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyRepeatFactor
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyRepeatFactor.description: The value of this object along with eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyType determines the effective repetition interval for this policy. The valid values are PolicyType RepeatFactor once 1 hourly 1 daily 1-2147483647 weekly 1-2147483647 monthly 1-2147483647 If the policy type is daily and the value of this object is 2, snapshots will be taken once in every 2 days.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStartTime.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStartTime
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStartTime.description: The value of this object represents the time to start creating snapshot(s) within a day expressed as number of minutes from 12:00AM. The maximum value for this column is 24*60-1 which represents 11:59PM.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEndTime.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEndTime
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEndTime.description: The value of this object represents the time to stop creating snapshot(s) within a day expressed as number of minutes from 12:00AM. The maximum value for this column is 24*60-1 which represents 11:59PM. If eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyType is once or hourly, the value of this column doesn't have any significance. If the value of this column is greater than start time, it represents end-time on the same day as start time. If the value is less than or equal to start time, it represents end-time on the next day of start time. This value doesnt have significance when frequency is set to zero. Endtime is exclusive when calculating no of snapshots. Example: StartTime EndTime Frequency NoofSnapshots 1320(10pm) 1380(11pm) 30mins 2 1320(10pm) 240(4am) 60mins 6 1320(10pm) 1320(10pm) 60mins 24 1320(10pm) 1319(9:59pm) 60mins 24 1320(10pm) - 0mins 1

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyTimeFrequenc.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyTimeFrequency
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyTimeFrequenc.description: The value of this object determines how frequent snapshots must be taken between start time and end time. This value doesn't have significance when policy type is set to once. For other policytypes, the value of end time is exclusive. For example if starttime is 180 (3:00AM) and endtime is 240(4:00AM), when frequency is set to 30, snapshots will be created at 3:00AM, 3:30AM. If the value is zero, it represents invalid frequency and in such case, end time doesnt have significance.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStartDate.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStartDate
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyStartDate.description: The value of this object determines the date from which the policy will be active. By default, this is the policy creation date. The value is expressed as number of days since epoch.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEndDate.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEndDate
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyEndDate.description: The value of this object determines the date after which the policy will be inactive.It doesnt have significance when policy type is once. Default value is the mamixum value allowed. When set to maximum value, the policy will be active until it gets deleted. The value is expressed as number of days since epoch.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyWeekMask.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyWeekMask
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyWeekMask.description: The value of this column is significant only if policytype is set to weekly or monthly. When the value is 0x7fffffff, it represents a special meaning to the value of occurence. See the description for occurence below. The LSB to LSB+6 bits of the mask are significant. Each bit represents a day in the week with LSB being Mon and LSB+6 being Sun. If mask is 0x00000041 - snapshots will be created on Monday and Sunday. If mask is 0x0000007f - snapshots will be created on all weekdays which is effectively a daily policy. If mask is 0x0000001f, it represents week days.If mask is 0x00000060, it represents weekend days.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyMonthMask.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyMonthMask
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyMonthMask.description: The value of this column is currently not being used.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyNextCreate.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyNextCreate
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyNextCreate.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The value of this column represents number of seconds since epoch at which the next snapshot by this policy is going to be created.

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyOccurence.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyOccurence
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyOccurence.description: The value of this column is significant only if the policy type is set to monthly. If weekmask is set to 0x7fffffff, the value of this column represents the occurence of a day with in a month. Example:If the value of this column is 5, it represents 5th day of the month. When the week mask is set to a value other than 0x7fffffff, the value of this column defines the occurence of a day as defined by weekmask. Example: When weekmask is set to 0x00000001 (Monday) and value of this column represents the following. Value Meaning 0x1 First monday of the month 0x2 Second monday of the month 0x3 Third monday of the month 0x4 Fourth monday of the month 0x7fffffff Last monday of the month

eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyReplication.name: eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyReplication
eqliscsiSnapCollectionPolicyReplication.description: When a row is created with this object set to a non-zero value, and a replication relationship has been configured for all volumes in the volume collection, the snapshots created will be queued to be replicated to the remote location as defined by the corresponding entry in the site table. The value for this object cannot be changed once the schedule is created. All the volumes in this collection must be replicating to the same partner.

eqliscsiVolColReplDeletionPolicy.name: eqliscsiVolColReplDeletionPolicy

The choices are as follows: local_only: Only the local references to the remote replica set collection will be removed. The remote replica set collection will remain intact and will need to be managed at the remote site. remote: The remote replica set collection will be deleted. This will destroy all of the remote data. Note that setting the value to 'remote' will cause the delete operation to fail if there is no connectivity to the remote site. If the deletion needs to proceed regardless of the state of the remote site, the local_only policy shoud be used

eqliscsiReplicantSiteStatusMajorVersion.name: eqliscsiReplicantSiteStatusMajorVersion

eqliscsiReplicantSiteStatusMaintVersion.description: This variable specifies the Maintenance part of the lowest member software version of the remote replication site group.

eqliscsiVolumeTaskStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Storage Volume Operations Status Table.

eqliscsiVolumeTaskStatusEntry.description: An entry (row) containing status for volume operations.

eqliscsiVolumeTaskStatusErrorCode.name: eqliscsiVolumeTaskStatusErrorCode
eqliscsiVolumeTaskStatusErrorCode.description: Error if any occurred while executing the task on this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeTemplateThinClonesTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeTemplateThinClonesTable
eqliscsiVolumeTemplateThinClonesTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Storage Template Thin Clone Table

eqliscsiVolumeTemplateThinClonesEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeTemplateThinClonesEntry
eqliscsiVolumeTemplateThinClonesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing a templates thin clone info. The first 2 indices are the volume index of the template volume and the second 2 indicies are the volume index of the thin clone.

eqliscsiThinCloneLocalMemberId.name: eqliscsiThinCloneLocalMemberId

eqliscsiThinCloneVolumeIndex.name: eqliscsiThinCloneVolumeIndex
eqliscsiThinCloneVolumeIndex.description: This field specifies the second part of a unique index for identifing a thin clone.

eqliscsiVolumeAdminAccountRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiTemplateVolumeStatusNumThinClone.description: This field represents the number of thin clones associated with a template volume.

eqliscsiTemplateVolumeStatusNumThinClone.description: This field represents the number of thin clone replicators associated with a template volume.

eqliscsiTemplateVolumeStatusNumThinClone.description: This field represents the number of thin clone replica sets associated with a template volume.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatisticsTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic This table contains a list inbound-replica sets and their statistics.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsCmdPdus.description: The count of Command PDUs transferred to this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsRspPdus.description: The count of Response PDUs transferred to this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsRxData.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsRxData
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsRxData.description: The count of data octets that were received by the local iSCSI node.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsNoOfSessions.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsNoOfSessions
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsNoOfSessions.description: No of sessions that were established and closed so far to this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsReadLatency.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsReadLatency
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsReadLatency.description: The accumulative latency in milli seconds for read operations on this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteLatency.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteLatency
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteLatency.description: The accumulative latency in milli seconds for write operations on this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsReadOpCount.description: The number of read operations on this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteOpCount.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteOpCount
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteOpCount.description: The number of write operations on this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsReadAvgLaten.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsReadAvgLatency
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsReadAvgLaten.description: The average latency in milli seconds for read operations on this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteAvgLate.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteAvgLatency
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsWriteAvgLate.description: The average latency in milli seconds for write operations on this snapshot.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsIscsiReadWri.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsIscsiReadWriteCmdsReceived
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsIscsiReadWri.description: The number of iscsi read/write commands received for operations on this volume. This object is a 64-bit version of eqliscsiVolumeStatsIscsiREadWriteCmdsReceived.

eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsIscsiTotalQD.name: eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsIscsiTotalQD
eqliscsiSnapAccumulatedStatsIscsiTotalQD.description: A 64-bit counter that is incremented by the current number of outstanding iSCSI IO operations each time an iSCSI IO is received by the target. The iSCSI IO operations include both reads and writes. This counter when divided by the total number of iSCSI IO operations provides the average queue depth. This object is a 64 bit version of eqliscsiVolumeStatsIscsiReadWriteCmdsCompleted.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountTable
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Admin Account Replication Site Table. This table contains a list of privilege matchings of administrative accounts and the replication sites those administrators have access to.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountEntry
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountEntry.description: An entry (row) containing mapping of administrative accounts and their replication site access.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountRowSta.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountRowSta.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountQuotaT.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountQuotaType
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountQuotaT.description: The format of the adminQuota value: 0 - Unlimited quota, 1 - Size in Megabytes. This field applies only to Volume Administrators.

eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountQuota.name: eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountQuota
eqliscsiVolumeReplSiteAdminAccountQuota.description: This field specifies the storage space quota (in MB) for a Volume Administrator in the delegated space at this replication site. This field applies only to Volume Administrators.

eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteTable.name: eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteTable
eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Group LDAP login access table. For LDAP login access configured with volume-admin privilege stores the replication sites, volume-admin has access to.

eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteEntry.name: eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteEntry
eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteEntry.description: An entry (row) containing the configuration for the LDAP login access replication quotas.

eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteQuotaType.name: eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteQuotaType
eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteQuotaType.description: The format of the adminQuota value: 0 - Unlimited quota, 1 - Size in Megabytes. This field applies only to Volume Administrators.

eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteQuota.name: eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteQuota
eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteQuota.description: This field specifies the storage space quota (in MB) for a Volume Administrator in the storage Repl Site. This field applies only to Volume Administrators.

eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteRowStatus.name: eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteRowStatus
eqlLdapLoginAccessReplSiteRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtensionEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtensionEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtensionEntry.description: An entry (row) containing volume-specific information required for configuring synchronous replication

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtRowStatus.description: This field is used to indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtSyncReplLocalMe.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtSyncReplLocalMemberId
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtSyncReplLocalMe.description: This field specifies the first part of a unique index for identifing a synchronous replication relationship between volumes.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtSyncReplIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtSyncReplIndex
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtSyncReplIndex.description: This field specifies the second part of a unique index for identifing a synchronous replication relationship between volumes.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtIntTargetIscsiN.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtIntTargetIscsiName
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplExtIntTargetIscsiN.description: This field specifies the iSCSI target name that is internally used for a syncronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplEntry.description: An entry (row) containing configuration information for replicating an active volume to a standby

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplRowStatus.description: This field is used to indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplLocalMemberId.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplLocalMemberId
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplLocalMemberId.description: This field specifies the first part of a unique index for identifing a synchronous replication relationship between volumes.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndex
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndex.description: This field specifies the second part of a unique index for identifing a synchronous replication relationship between volumes.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPaused.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPaused
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPaused.description: Indicates whether IO forwarding to the replication standby volume is allowed (false) or halted (true).

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing peer volume information for synchronous volume replication. The first 2 indexes identify the volume, and the second 2 indexes identify the peer.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerLocalMemberId.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerLocalMemberId
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerLocalMemberId.description: This field specifies the first part of a unique index for identifing the peer of the synchronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerVolIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerVolIndex
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerVolIndex.description: This field specifies the second part of a unique index for identifing the peer of the synchronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerPsvId.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerPsvId
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplPeerPsvId.description: If non-zero, the value represents the PsvId of the peer of the synchronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusSyncStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusSyncStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusSyncStatus.description: This field specifies whether the volume is in sync

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusUnreplicated.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusUnreplicatedChanges
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusUnreplicated.description: This field specifies whether unreplicated changes exist for this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusTotalTxDataM.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusTotalTxDataMB
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusTotalTxDataM.description: This field represents the amount of total changes since last in sync.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusRemainingTxD.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusRemainingTxDataMB
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplStatusRemainingTxD.description: This field represents the amount of remaining changes which need to be replicated.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualTable
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Sync Replication Virtual Volume Table. This table contains a list of sync replication virtual volumes in a group and their attributes.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualEntry.description: An entry (row) containing sync replication virtual volume info.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualAccessType.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualAccessType
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualAccessType.description: This field specifies access rights for the volume. The volume can be either read-write or read-only. The default is read-write.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualAdminStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualAdminStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualAdminStatus.description: This field specifies if the volume is set to online or offline by the administrator. If a volume is offline, it cannot be accessed by iscsi initiators.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualMultInitiat.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualMultInitiator
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualMultInitiat.description: Specifies if the access from multiple initiators is allowed for the volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusTable
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Sync Replication Virtual Volume Table. This table contains a list of sync replication virtual volumes in a group and their stats.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusEntry.description: An entry (row) containing sync replication virtual volume stats.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusReser.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusReservedSpace
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusReser.description: This field specifies how many MB of space is reserved for snapshots of this volume. This is a dynamic value, it is not Administrator setable.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusReser.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusReservedSpaceAvail
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusReser.description: This field specifies how many MB of reserved space that is unused by the snapshots.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusNumSn.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusNumSnapshots
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusNumSn.description: Indicates the number of snapshots that the system is maintaining on the specified volume

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusOperS.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusOperStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusOperS.description: This field specifies the current operational status of the volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusConne.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusConnections
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusConne.description: The value of this object represents number of active iscsi connections to this volume. It MUST match with the number of rows for this particular iscsiNode in iscsiConnectionAttributesTable.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusAlloc.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusAllocatedSpace
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusAlloc.description: The value of this object represents the actual materialized pages for this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusVolRe.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusVolReserveSpace
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusVolRe.description: The value of this object represents the pages reserved for this volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusExtCo.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusExtConnections
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatusExtCo.description: The value of this object represents number of active iscsi connections to this volume, not counting EQL generated connections.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatisticsT.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatisticsTable
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatisticsT.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Sync Replication Virtual Volume Table. This table contains a list of sync replication virtual volumes in a group and their statistics.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatisticsE.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatisticsEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatisticsE.description: An entry (row) containing sync replication virtual volume statistics.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatsTxData.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatsTxData
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatsTxData.description: The count of data octets that were transmitted by the local iSCSI node.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatsRxData.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatsRxData
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplVirtualStatsRxData.description: The count of data octets that were received by the local iSCSI node.

eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusTable.name: eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusTable
eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Sync Replication Virtual Volume Sync Repl Status Table. This table contains a list of sync replication virtual volumes in a group and their sync replication status.

eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusEntry.name: eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusEntry
eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusEntry.description: An entry (row) containing sync replication virtual volume sync replication status.

eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusSyncStat.name: eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusSyncStatus
eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusSyncStat.description: This field specifies whether the volume is in sync.

eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusUnreplic.name: eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusUnreplicatedChanges
eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusUnreplic.description: This field specifies whether unreplicated changes exist for this volume.

eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusTotalTxD.name: eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusTotalTxDataMB
eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusTotalTxD.description: This field represents the amount of total changes since last in sync.

eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusRemainin.name: eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusRemainingTxDataMB
eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplStatusRemainin.description: This field represents the amount of remaining changes which need to be replicated.

eqliscsiSyncReplAfoStateEntry.name: eqliscsiSyncReplAfoStateEntry
eqliscsiSyncReplAfoStateEntry.description: An member local entry (row) containing a volume's AFO state for synchronous replication The first 4 indexes identify the volume with the lowest psvid, and the second 4 indexes identify the volume with the highest psvid.

eqliscsiSyncReplAfoSeqNum.name: eqliscsiSyncReplAfoSeqNum
eqliscsiSyncReplAfoSeqNum.description: This field specifies the sequence number for the record

eqliscsiSyncReplAfoState.name: eqliscsiSyncReplAfoState
eqliscsiSyncReplAfoState.description: This field specifies the current AFO state

eqliscsiSyncReplAfoGrpLeadUuid.name: eqliscsiSyncReplAfoGrpLeadUuid
eqliscsiSyncReplAfoGrpLeadUuid.description: This value represents the UUID of the Group lead that wrote this record

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolT.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolTable
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolT.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains the list of pool configuration for each sync-repl collection.

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolR.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolRowStatus
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolR.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolI.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolIndex
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolI.description: This field specifies the unique index of the pool serving as the active pool in a sync-replication collection

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolF.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolFlags
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplActivePoolF.description: This fields defines the common place holder for sync-replication volume collection. The flags must be of type enable(1) or disable(0), and the default will always be disable(0).

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusSyncS.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusSyncStatus
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusSyncS.description: This field specifies whether the collection is in sync

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusUnrep.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusUnreplicatedChanges
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusUnrep.description: This field specifies whether unreplicated changes exist for this collection

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusTotal.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusTotalTxDataMB
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusTotal.description: This field represents the amount of total changes since last in sync for this collection

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusRemai.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusRemainingTxDataMB
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplStatusRemai.description: This field represents the amount of remaining changes which need to be replicated for this collection

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesTable
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Sync replication index volumes table. Provides relationships between sync replication indexes and all the volumes that are associated with that index.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing volume information for synchronous replication access/alternate pairs. The first two parts of the index identify the sync repl index of the pair, and the second two parts of the index identify the volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesPsvId.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesPsvId
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplIndexVolumesPsvId.description: If non-zero, the value represents the PsvId of the peer of the synchronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplSyncActiveOfflineE.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplSyncActiveOfflineEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplSyncActiveOfflineE.description: An entry (row) containing volume-specific information used to set the identified Synchronous Replication volume offline.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplSyncActiveOffline.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplSyncActiveOffline
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplSyncActiveOffline.description: This field is used to take the SyncActive volume offline. This field is read-write.

eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoEntry.name: eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoEntry
eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoEntry.description: An entry (row) containing information about a volume at the time it was deleted, used to restore a deleted volume to its original state (on un-delete), or to purge volume permanently to create free space.

eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoRowStatus.name: eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoRowStatus
eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoRowStatus.description: This field is used to indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoOriginalName.name: eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoOriginalName
eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoOriginalName.description: This field is the original name of the volume at the time it was deleted. A unique name is created for a deleted volume so that it does not collide with visible volumes. The volume is restored with this original name if possible.

eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoOriginalType.name: eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoOriginalType
eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoOriginalType.description: This field specifies the volume type at the time it was deleted. Volumes are converted to thin provisioned when they are deleted in order to consume as little free space as possible. They are converted back to this type when they are restored.

eqliscsiDeletedVolumeFlags.name: eqliscsiDeletedVolumeFlags
eqliscsiDeletedVolumeFlags.description: This bitfield contains volume modifiers or types that a volume originally had at the time it was deleted. Deleted volumes are converted to thin-provisioned while recoverable, these fields help to restore a volume to its original state.

eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoDeleteDate.name: eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoDeleteDate
eqliscsiDeletedVolumeInfoDeleteDate.description: This field specifies the deleted time for a volume. Time is represented as the time in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC, 1970-01-01. It is used to determine the oldest deleted volume when it is necessary to trim back volumes to create free space.

eqliscsiDeletedVolumeThinWarnPercentage.name: eqliscsiDeletedVolumeThinWarnPercentage
eqliscsiDeletedVolumeThinWarnPercentage.description: This field is the original thin warning percentage for the volume at the time it was deleted.

eqliscsiDeletedVolumeThinMaxGrowPercenta.name: eqliscsiDeletedVolumeThinMaxGrowPercentage
eqliscsiDeletedVolumeThinMaxGrowPercenta.description: This field is the original thin max grow percentage for the volume at the time it was deleted.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerTable
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains the volume index of the volume in the active pool for a sync-repl volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing active peer volume information for synchronous volume replication.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerRowStatu.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerRowStatu.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLocalMem.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLocalMemberId
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLocalMem.description: This field specifies the first part of a unique index for identifing the active peer of the synchronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerVolIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerVolIndex
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerVolIndex.description: This field specifies the second part of a unique index for identifing the active peer of the synchronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerFlags.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerFlags
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerFlags.description: This field defines the common place holder for sync-replication volume. The flags must be of type enable(1) or disable(0), and the default will always be disable(0).

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupEn.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupEn.description: An entry (row) containing active peer volume information for synchronous volume replication. The index identifies any peer, and the columns identify the active peer, or 0 if there is none.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupLo.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupLocalMemberId
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupLo.description: This field specifies the first part of a unique index for identifing the active peer of the synchronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupVo.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupVolIndex
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplActivePeerLookupVo.description: This field specifies the second part of a unique index for identifing the active peer of the synchronous replication volume.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackTable
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table maintains the list of underlying sync-repl volumes and if they can be used as a sync-repl failback target.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackEntry
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackEntry.description: An entry in the sync-repl failback table.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplFailbackRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this table entry.

eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplAllowFailback.name: eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplAllowFailback
eqliscsiVolumeSyncReplAllowFailback.description: This field is used to indicate that this volume can be used as a failback target.

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveO.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveOfflineEntry
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveO.description: An entry (row) containing pool-specific information used to set the identified Synchronous Replication pool offline.

eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveO.name: eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveOffline
eqliscsiVolCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveO.description: This field is used to take the collection SyncActive pool offline. This field is read-write.

eqliscsiSyncReplStateEntry.name: eqliscsiSyncReplStateEntry
eqliscsiSyncReplStateEntry.description: An member local entry (row) containing a volume's synchronous replication state The first 4 indexes identify the volume with the lowest psvid, and the second 4 indexes identify the volume with the highest psvid.

eqliscsiSyncReplStateSeqNum.name: eqliscsiSyncReplStateSeqNum
eqliscsiSyncReplStateSeqNum.description: This field specifies the sequence number for the record

eqliscsiSyncReplStateState.name: eqliscsiSyncReplStateState
eqliscsiSyncReplStateState.description: This field specifies the Sync Rep State for the volume

eqliscsiSyncReplStateGrpLeadUuid.name: eqliscsiSyncReplStateGrpLeadUuid
eqliscsiSyncReplStateGrpLeadUuid.description: This value represents the UUID of the Group lead that wrote this record

eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplSyncActiveOffl.name: eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplSyncActiveOfflineEntry
eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplSyncActiveOffl.description: An entry (row) containing volume-specific information used to set the identified Synchronous Replication volume offline for a virtual volume.

eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplSyncActiveOffl.name: eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplSyncActiveOffline
eqliscsiVsrVirtualSyncReplSyncActiveOffl.description: This field is used to get the SyncActive offline status for the sync-rep volume pair represented by the virtual volume. This field is read-only, the value can only be set via the volume SyncActive offline table.

eqliscsiVsrCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveO.name: eqliscsiVsrCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveOfflineEntry
eqliscsiVsrCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveO.description: An entry (row) containing pool-specific information used to read the identified Synchronous Replication pool offline.

eqliscsiVsrCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveO.name: eqliscsiVsrCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveOffline
eqliscsiVsrCollectionSyncReplSyncActiveO.description: This field is used to get the SyncActive offline status for the sync-rep collection represented by the virtual collection This field is read-only, the value can only be set via the volume SyncActive offline collection table.

eqliscsiVolNameSecondaryIndexEntry.name: eqliscsiVolNameSecondaryIndexEntry
eqliscsiVolNameSecondaryIndexEntry.description: An entry (row) which uses the eqliscsiVolumeName secondary key to lookup a eqliscsiVolumeName.

eqliscsiVolNameSecondaryIndexRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolNameSecondaryIndexRowStatus
eqliscsiVolNameSecondaryIndexRowStatus.description: This field is value of the RowStatus of the corresponding eqliscsiVolumeRowStatus volume

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetTable.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetTable
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Table Volume set table. This table stores information about Shared Volume Sets in the PS-Group

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetEntry.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetEntry
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetEntry.description: An entry (row) containing shared volume set information.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetIndex.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetIndex
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifing shared volume set.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetRowStatus.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetRowStatus
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetRowStatus.description: This field indicates whether the shared volume set is active or not.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetPsvid.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetPsvid
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetPsvid.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field is for internal use only.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetSectorSize.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetSectorSize
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetSectorSize.description: This field specifies, in bytes, the sector size all shared volumes in this shared volume set.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetStorageBucketUUID.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetStorageBucketUUID
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetStorageBucketUUID.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY A pointer to the parent storage bucket that contains this shared volume set.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSharedVolumeSetBucke.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSharedVolumeSetBucket
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSharedVolumeSetBucke.description: A pointer to the parent storage bucket that contains this shared volume set. Note this is a redundant field the StorageBucketUUID field stores the same information. But the UUID field will come out as soon we add the support so IOM can read this table through netmgtd.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetBucketFullPolicy.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetBucketFullPolicy
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSetBucketFullPolicy.description: This field specifies how the firmware will handle the bucket full condition. keep-online-fail-write-to-new-pages: Keep all the shared volumes in the shared volume set online, but fail all write to unallocated pages. make-svs-offline: Take all the shared volumes in the shared volume set offline.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeTable.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeTable
eqliscsiSharedVolumeTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Table for storing shared volume set attributes that can frequently change.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeEntry.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeEntry
eqliscsiSharedVolumeEntry.description: An entry (row) containing status for shared volume the values in this table are user configurable.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeIndex.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeIndex
eqliscsiSharedVolumeIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying a shared volume.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeRowStatus.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeRowStatus
eqliscsiSharedVolumeRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqliscsiSharedVolumePsvid.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumePsvid
eqliscsiSharedVolumePsvid.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field is a unique universal identifier for this shared volume. This field is mostly for internal use only.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeName.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeName
eqliscsiSharedVolumeName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies a user friendly name for the shared volume. The name must be unique within a group. The name must not contain spaces or special characters. The name can be up to 64 characters in length. There is no default.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSize.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSize
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSize.description: This field specifies the volume size in MB. There is no default. Note: Volume size is round to a multiple of 15MB. All shared volumes are thin provisioned so this value represents the advertized size of the volume

eqliscsiSharedVolumeCreatedAs.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeCreatedAs
eqliscsiSharedVolumeCreatedAs.description: This field specifies if the shared volume is set to online or offline by the administrator. If a volume is offline, it cannot be accessed by iscsi initiators.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeIfSnapshotOrFastClon.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeIfSnapshotOrFastCloneMyParentVVol
eqliscsiSharedVolumeIfSnapshotOrFastClon.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field is only applicable to shared volumes that are created as snapshots. If snapshot shared volume, this field identifies the parent.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSharedVolumeSet.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSharedVolumeSet
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSharedVolumeSet.description: A pointer to the corresponding Shared Volume Set that contains this shared volume.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeDescription.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeDescription
eqliscsiSharedVolumeDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details about the volume. The description can be up to 128 characters. There is no default value.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeFlags.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeFlags
eqliscsiSharedVolumeFlags.description: This fields defines the common place holder for Volume operational flags.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeSecondaryLunId.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeSecondaryLunId
eqliscsiSharedVolumeSecondaryLunId.description: This field specifies the secondary LUN id for the volume This is an auto-generated field for internal use only.

eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeTable.name: eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeTable
eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Table for storing vmWare specific for virtual volume. Note all virtual volumes are implemented as shared volumes. This table stores information that is not used by the PS-Group and is only used by vmware.

eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeEntry.name: eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeEntry
eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeEntry.description: An entry (row) containing information used by vmWare for this virtual volume. Note columns in this table are not used by PS-Group, for the most purpose they are opaque for the PS-Group. They only persist information relevant to vmWare

eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeRowStatus.name: eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeRowStatus
eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeType.name: eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeType
eqlVmwareVirtualVolumeType.description: This field specifies vmware virtual volume type.

eqlVmWareVirtualVolumeIfSnapshotCreateDa.name: eqlVmWareVirtualVolumeIfSnapshotCreateDate
eqlVmWareVirtualVolumeIfSnapshotCreateDa.description: This field specifies the time at which this snapshot was created Time is represented as the time in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC, 1970-01-01. It is meant to be used by the VASA provider to cleanup all the in-progress snapshots that were never completed by VMware

eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusTable.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusTable
eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Storage Volume Table. This table contains a list of volumes in a group and their stats.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusAllocatedSpace.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusAllocatedSpace
eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusAllocatedSpace.description: The value of this object represents the actual materialized pages for this volume.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusSharedSpace.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusSharedSpace
eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusSharedSpace.description: This field represents the number of pages the volume shares with other shared volumes.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusOperStatus.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusOperStatus
eqliscsiSharedVolumeStatusOperStatus.description: This field specifies the current operational status of the shared volume.

eqliscsiDynVVolTable.name: eqliscsiDynVVolTable
eqliscsiDynVVolTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic VVol Table. This table is a Dyn table used by clients only to CREATE or DELETE VVol entries. The information contained in this table corresponds to fields present in the eqliscsiVolumeTable and the eqlVVolTable. A successful CREATE on this table will result in CREATION of rows in eqliscsiVolumeTable and eqlVVolTable. A successful DELETE on this table will result in DELETION of rows in eqliscsiVolumeTable and eqlVVolTable. TimeoutCreate:60

eqliscsiDynVVolEntry.name: eqliscsiDynVVolEntry
eqliscsiDynVVolEntry.description: An entry (row) containing the Dyn VVol Information.

eqliscsiDynVVolRowStatus.name: eqliscsiDynVVolRowStatus
eqliscsiDynVVolRowStatus.description: This field indicates whether the VVol row is ACTIVE or not.

eqliscsiDynVVolName.name: eqliscsiDynVVolName
eqliscsiDynVVolName.description: This field specifies a user friendly name for a VVol. The name must be unique within a group. The name must not contain spaces or special characters. The name can be up to 64 characters in length. There is no default.

eqliscsiDynVVolSize.name: eqliscsiDynVVolSize
eqliscsiDynVVolSize.description: This field specifies the VVol size in MB. There is no default. Note: VVol size is round to a multiple of 15MB.

eqliscsiDynVVolContainer.name: eqliscsiDynVVolContainer
eqliscsiDynVVolContainer.description: This field contains the index of the container to place this VVol in.

eqliscsiDynVVolDesc.name: eqliscsiDynVVolDesc
eqliscsiDynVVolDesc.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details about the volume. The description can be up to 128 characters. There is no default value.

eqliscsiDynVVolCreatedAs.name: eqliscsiDynVVolCreatedAs
eqliscsiDynVVolCreatedAs.description: This field specifies how this virtual volume was created.

eqliscsiDynVVolIfSnapshotOrFastCloneMyPa.name: eqliscsiDynVVolIfSnapshotOrFastCloneMyParentVVol
eqliscsiDynVVolIfSnapshotOrFastCloneMyPa.description: Only applicable if vvol was created as a snapshot or a fast-clone. Gives information about the parent VVol.

eqliscsiDynVVolType.name: eqliscsiDynVVolType
eqliscsiDynVVolType.description: This field stores the type of the VVol.

eqliscsiDynVVolCreateIsDerived.name: eqliscsiDynVVolCreateIsDerived
eqliscsiDynVVolCreateIsDerived.description: Truth value only applicable on VVol create request, used to indicate if the new VVol to create is a derived VVol.

eqliscsiDynVVolCreateDerivedType.name: eqliscsiDynVVolCreateDerivedType
eqliscsiDynVVolCreateDerivedType.description: Only applicable when creating new vvols and if Dervied is true, indicates how the new VVol should be derived from the parent VVol

eqliscsiDynVVolCreateDerivedFromParent.name: eqliscsiDynVVolCreateDerivedFromParent
eqliscsiDynVVolCreateDerivedFromParent.description: Only applicable when creating new vvols and if isDerived is true, contains the index of the volume to derive from.

eqliscsiDynVVolIfSnapshotMyStatus.name: eqliscsiDynVVolIfSnapshotMyStatus
eqliscsiDynVVolIfSnapshotMyStatus.description: This field specifies the snapshot status if the virtual volume, is a snapshot of another volume.

eqliscsiDynVVolPsvid.name: eqliscsiDynVVolPsvid
eqliscsiDynVVolPsvid.description: This is read-only field, it stores the unique universal identifier for this Virtual volume.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyTable.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyTable
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic shared volume rollback table. This table is a dynamic table used by clients rollback a shared volume to a snapshot shared volume.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyEntry.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyEntry
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyEntry.description: An entry (row) containing the dynamic VVol Information.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyRowStatus.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyRowStatus
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyDestSharedVolu.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyDestSharedVolume
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopyDestSharedVolu.description: This field identifes the destination of the rollback.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopySourceSharedVo.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopySourceSharedVolume
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeCopySourceSharedVo.description: This field identifes the destination of the rollback.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindTable.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindTable
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic shared volume bind unbind table This write-only table is a dynamic table used by clients to bind a shared volume to a host.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindEntry.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindEntry
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindEntry.description: An entry (row) containing the dynamic VVol Information.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindRowStatu.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindRowStatus
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindRowStatu.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindOper.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindOper
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindOper.description: This field identifes the bind/unbind operation

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindAccessGr.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindAccessGroupIndex
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindAccessGr.description: This field identifes the host/access group to bind this shared volume to.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindOperAugm.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindOperAugment
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeBindUnbindOperAugm.description: This field identifes the bind/unbind augemented operation. 0,1 are used to make sure the ACL fields are updated/created. Option 2 make it so that we DO NOT cleanup ACL's. This would be used for member down status

eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataTable.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataTable
eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Table for storing metadata of shared volumes.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataEntry.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataEntry
eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataEntry.description: Each entry represents a key-value pair combination for a shared volume. Each shared volume may have several key-value properties in which case a shared volume will be represented by more than one entry where each entry is a specific key-value pair (metadata).

eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataRowStatus.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataRowStatus
eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataRowStatus.description: This field is used to indicate the status of the shared volume metadata entry.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataIndex.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataIndex
eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying the shared volume metadata.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataKey.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataKey
eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataKey.description: Key represents the metadata field name. The maximum supported length of this field including the NULL character is 65.

eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataValue.name: eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataValue
eqliscsiSharedVolumeMetadataValue.description: This field represents the value of the metadata field. The maximum supported length of this field including the NULL character is 255.

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolTable.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolTable
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Table for storing virtual volumes that represent prepped snapshots. Note this is a transient state, VMWare creates snapshots in 2 steps 1) prepareToSnapshotVirtualVolume 2) snapshotVirtualVolume This table stages all the VVOLS all the Virtual volumes that were created as a result of the 1st step. Once the 2nd step is executed these virtual volumes will transition into being real Shared Volumes on the equallogic PS-Group. Entries in this table use the same index as the shared volume table, because VMware requires that PS-Group generate the volume identifier in step 1 and it will use this identifier for all forthcoming operations to this volume. Entries in this table will have a corressponding entry in the VmwareVirtualTable this table keeps track of the VVOL Type (config, data, swap)

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolEntry.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolEntry
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolEntry.description: An entry (row) containing status for shared volume the values in this table are user configurable.

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolRowStatus.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolRowStatus
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolPsvid.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolPsvid
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolPsvid.description: This field is a unique universal identifier for this shared volume. This field is mostly for internal use only.

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolName.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolName
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies a user friendly name for the shared volume. The name must be unique within a group. The name must not contain spaces or special characters. The name can be up to 64 characters in length. There is no default.

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolSize.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolSize
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolSize.description: This field specifies the volume size in MB. There is no default. Note: Volume size is round to a multiple of 15MB. All shared volumes are thin provisioned so this value represents the advertized size of the volume

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolMyParentVVol.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolMyParentVVol
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolMyParentVVol.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field is only applicable to shared volumes that are created as snapshots. If snapshot shared volume, this field identifies the parent.

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolBucket.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolBucket
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolBucket.description: This field contains the index of the bucket that contains this prepped snapshot.

eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolDescription.name: eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolDescription
eqlPreppedSnapshotVVolDescription.description: This field specifies a descriptive string that provides details about the volume. The description can be up to 128 characters. There is no default value.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffTable.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffTable
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic shared volume difference table This write-only table is a dynamic table used by clients to perform a difference between 2 volumes

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffEntry.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffEntry
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffEntry.description: An entry (row) containing the dynamic row. The Index will be the VVol

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffRowStatus.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffRowStatus
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffBaseIndex.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffBaseIndex
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffBaseIndex.description: This field specifies the base shared volume index associated with the shared volume.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffAdmin.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffAdmin
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffAdmin.description: This field identifes the type of diff ooperation

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffStartSegmentOf.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffStartSegmentOffset
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffStartSegmentOf.description: This value represents the starting segment for the diff operation

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffSegmentsLength.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffSegmentsLength
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffSegmentsLength.description: This value represents the segments size being requested.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkSize.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkSize
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkSize.description: This value represents the size of the Chunk entry for the bit map or other calculation

eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationTa.name: eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationTable
eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationTa.description: EqualLogic-Persistent This table defines volume specific compression paramters.

eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationEn.name: eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationEntry
eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationEn.description: An entry in the volume compression configuration table.

eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationRo.name: eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationRo.description: This field is used indicate the status of this table entry.

eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationPo.name: eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationPolicy
eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationPo.description: Specify how this volume's snapshots should be compressed.

eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationSn.name: eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationSnapDelay
eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationSn.description: The value of this object represents how long to wait prior to marking a snapshot as eligible for compression. Current default is 24 hours. Only used when eqliscsiVolumeCompressionConfigurationPolicy is set to user-defined.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkTable.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkTable
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic. This table exposes the vvol as number of chunks.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkIndex.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkIndex
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkIndex.description: This value represents index of the chunk.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkSegmentSi.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkSegmentSize
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkSegmentSi.description: This value represents the size of a segment. This is passed in to the row create of the eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkTable

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffNumChunkSegmen.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffNumChunkSegments
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffNumChunkSegmen.description: This value represents the size of the chunk expressed as number of segments.

eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkModified.name: eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkModified
eqlDynamicSharedVolumeDiffChunkModified.description: This value represents a bit mask of modified segments in the given chunk.

eqliscsiVolumeMetadataTable.name: eqliscsiVolumeMetadataTable
eqliscsiVolumeMetadataTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Table for storing metadata of volumes.

eqliscsiVolumeMetadataEntry.name: eqliscsiVolumeMetadataEntry
eqliscsiVolumeMetadataEntry.description: Each entry represents a key-value pair combination for a volume. Each volume may have several key-value properties in which case a volume will be represented by more than one entry where each entry is a specific key-value pair (metadata).

eqliscsiVolumeMetadataRowStatus.name: eqliscsiVolumeMetadataRowStatus
eqliscsiVolumeMetadataRowStatus.description: This field is used to indicate the status of the volume metadata entry.

eqliscsiVolumeMetadataIndex.name: eqliscsiVolumeMetadataIndex
eqliscsiVolumeMetadataIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying the volume metadata.

eqliscsiVolumeMetadataKey.name: eqliscsiVolumeMetadataKey
eqliscsiVolumeMetadataKey.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY Key represents the metadata field name. The maximum supported length of this field including the NULL character is 65.

eqliscsiVolumeMetadataValue.name: eqliscsiVolumeMetadataValue
eqliscsiVolumeMetadataValue.description: This field represents the value of the metadata field. The maximum supported length of this field including the NULL character is 255.

eqliscsiSnapshotMetadataTable.name: eqliscsiSnapshotMetadataTable
eqliscsiSnapshotMetadataTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Table for storing metadata of snapshots.

eqliscsiSnapshotMetadataEntry.name: eqliscsiSnapshotMetadataEntry
eqliscsiSnapshotMetadataEntry.description: Each entry represents a key-value pair combination for a snapshot. Each snapshot may have several key-value properties in which case a snapshot will be represented by more than one entry where each entry is a specific key-value pair (metadata).

eqliscsiSnapshotMetadataRowStatus.name: eqliscsiSnapshotMetadataRowStatus
